83 // Check basic filter health metrics and return a consolidated health status
84 bool NavEKF_core::healthy(void) const
85 {
86  uint8_t faultInt;
87  getFilterFaults(faultInt);
88  if (faultInt > 0) {
89  return false;
90  }
91  if (frontend._fallback && velTestRatio > 1 && posTestRatio > 1 && hgtTestRatio > 1) {
92  // all three metrics being above 1 means the filter is
93  // extremely unhealthy.
94  return false;
95  }
96  // Give the filter a second to settle before use
97  if ((imuSampleTime_ms - ekfStartTime_ms) < 1000 ) {
98  return false;
99  }
100  // barometer and position innovations must be within limits when on-ground
101  float horizErrSq = sq(innovVelPos[3]) + sq(innovVelPos[4]);
102  if (!vehicleArmed && (!hgtHealth || fabsf(hgtInnovFiltState) > 1.0f || horizErrSq > 2.0f)) {
103  return false;
104  }
105 
106  // all OK
107  return true;
108 }

110 // resets position states to last GPS measurement or to zero if in constant position mode
111 void NavEKF_core::ResetPosition(void)
112 {
113  // Store the position before the reset so that we can record the reset delta
114  posResetNE.x = state.position.x;
115  posResetNE.y = state.position.y;
116 
117  if (constPosMode || (PV_AidingMode != AID_ABSOLUTE)) {
118  state.position.x = 0;
119  state.position.y = 0;
120  } else if (!gpsNotAvailable) {
121  // write to state vector and compensate for GPS latency
122  state.position.x = gpsPosNE.x + 0.001f*velNED.x*float(frontend._msecPosDelay);
123  state.position.y = gpsPosNE.y + 0.001f*velNED.y*float(frontend._msecPosDelay);
124  // the estimated states at the last GPS measurement are set equal to the GPS measurement to prevent transients on the first fusion
125  statesAtPosTime.position.x = gpsPosNE.x;
126  statesAtPosTime.position.y = gpsPosNE.y;
127  }
128  // stored horizontal position states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
129  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
130  storedStates[i].position.x = state.position.x;
131  storedStates[i].position.y = state.position.y;
132  }
133 
134  // Calculate the position jump due to the reset
135  posResetNE.x = state.position.x - posResetNE.x;
136  posResetNE.y = state.position.y - posResetNE.y;
137 
138  // store the time of the reset
139  lastPosReset_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
140 }

142 // Reset velocity states to last GPS measurement if available or to zero if in constant position mode or if PV aiding is not absolute
143 // Do not reset vertical velocity using GPS as there is baro alt available to constrain drift
144 void NavEKF_core::ResetVelocity(void)
145 {
146  // Store the velocity before the reset so that we can record the reset delta
147  velResetNE.x = state.velocity.x;
148  velResetNE.y = state.velocity.y;
149 
150  if (constPosMode || PV_AidingMode != AID_ABSOLUTE) {
151  state.velocity.zero();
152  state.vel1.zero();
153  state.vel2.zero();
154  posDownDerivative = 0.0f;
155  } else if (!gpsNotAvailable) {
156  // reset horizontal velocity states
157  state.velocity.x = velNED.x; // north velocity from blended accel data
158  state.velocity.y = velNED.y; // east velocity from blended accel data
159  state.vel1.x = velNED.x; // north velocity from IMU1 accel data
160  state.vel1.y = velNED.y; // east velocity from IMU1 accel data
161  state.vel2.x = velNED.x; // north velocity from IMU2 accel data
162  state.vel2.y = velNED.y; // east velocity from IMU2 accel data
163  // over write stored horizontal velocity states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
164  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
165  storedStates[i].velocity.x = velNED.x;
166  storedStates[i].velocity.y = velNED.y;
167  }
168  }
169 
170  // Calculate the velocity jump due to the reset
171  velResetNE.x = state.velocity.x - velResetNE.x;
172  velResetNE.y = state.velocity.y - velResetNE.y;
173 
174  // store the time of the reset
175  lastVelReset_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
176 }

178 // reset the vertical position state using the last height measurement
179 void NavEKF_core::ResetHeight(void)
180 {
181  // read the altimeter
182  readHgtData();
183  // write to the state vector
184  state.position.z = -hgtMea; // down position from blended accel data
185  state.posD1 = -hgtMea; // down position from IMU1 accel data
186  state.posD2 = -hgtMea; // down position from IMU2 accel data
187  terrainState = state.position.z + rngOnGnd;
188  // Reset the vertical velocity state using GPS vertical velocity if we are airborne (use arm status as a surrogate)
189  // Check that GPS vertical velocity data is available and can be used
190  if (vehicleArmed && !gpsNotAvailable && frontend._fusionModeGPS == 0) {
191  state.velocity.z = velNED.z;
192  }
193  // reset stored vertical position states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
194  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
195  storedStates[i].position.z = -hgtMea;
196  }
197  // reset the height state for the complementary filter used to provide a vertical position dervative
198  posDown = state.position.z;
199 }

201 // this function is used to initialise the filter whilst moving, using the AHRS DCM solution
202 // it should NOT be used to re-initialise after a timeout as DCM will also be corrupted
203 bool NavEKF_core::InitialiseFilterDynamic(void)
204 {
205  // Don't start if the user has disabled
206  if (frontend._enable == 0) {
207  return false;
208  }
209 
210  // this forces healthy() to be false so that when we ask for ahrs
211  // attitude we get the DCM attitude regardless of the state of AHRS_EKF_USE
212  statesInitialised = false;
213 
214  // If we are a plane and don't have GPS lock then don't initialise
215  if (assume_zero_sideslip() && _ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
216  return false;
217  }
218 
219  // If the DCM solution has not converged, then don't initialise
220  // If an extended time has passed we apply a looser check criteria because movement or GPS noise can be increase the errorRP value from DCM
221  if ((_ahrs->get_error_rp() > 0.05f && _ahrs->uptime_ms() < 30000U) || _ahrs->get_error_rp() > 0.1f) {
222  return false;
223  }
224 
225  // Set re-used variables to zero
226  InitialiseVariables();
227 
228  // get initial time deltat between IMU measurements (sec)
229  dtDelAng = dtIMUavg = 1.0f/_ahrs->get_ins().get_sample_rate();
230 
231  // set number of updates over which gps and baro measurements are applied to the velocity and position states
232  gpsUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecGpsAvg);
233  gpsUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/gpsUpdateCountMaxInv);
234  hgtUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecHgtAvg);
235  hgtUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/hgtUpdateCountMaxInv);
236  magUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecMagAvg);
237  magUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/magUpdateCountMaxInv);
238  flowUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecFlowAvg);
239  flowUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/flowUpdateCountMaxInv);
240 
241  // calculate initial orientation and earth magnetic field states
242  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(_ahrs->roll, _ahrs->pitch);
243 
244  // write to state vector
245  state.gyro_bias.zero();
246  state.accel_zbias1 = 0;
247  state.accel_zbias2 = 0;
248  state.wind_vel.zero();
249 
250  // read the GPS and set the position and velocity states
251  readGpsData();
252  ResetVelocity();
253  ResetPosition();
254 
255  // read the barometer and set the height state
256  readHgtData();
257  ResetHeight();
258 
259  // set stored states to current state
260  StoreStatesReset();
261 
262  // set to true now that states have be initialised
263  statesInitialised = true;
264 
265  // define Earth rotation vector in the NED navigation frame
266  calcEarthRateNED(earthRateNED, _ahrs->get_home().lat);
267 
268  // initialise IMU pre-processing states
269  readIMUData();
270 
271  // initialise the covariance matrix
272  CovarianceInit();
273 
274  return true;
275 }

277 // Initialise the states from accelerometer and magnetometer data (if present)
278 // This method can only be used when the vehicle is static
279 bool NavEKF_core::InitialiseFilterBootstrap(void)
280 {
281  // If we are a plane and don't have GPS lock then don't initialise
282  if (assume_zero_sideslip() && _ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
283  statesInitialised = false;
284  return false;
285  }
286 
287  // set re-used variables to zero
288  InitialiseVariables();
289 
290  // get initial time deltat between IMU measurements (sec)
291  dtDelAng = dtIMUavg = 1.0f/_ahrs->get_ins().get_sample_rate();
292 
293  // set number of updates over which gps and baro measurements are applied to the velocity and position states
294  gpsUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecGpsAvg);
295  gpsUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/gpsUpdateCountMaxInv);
296  hgtUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecHgtAvg);
297  hgtUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/hgtUpdateCountMaxInv);
298  magUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecMagAvg);
299  magUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/magUpdateCountMaxInv);
300 
301  // acceleration vector in XYZ body axes measured by the IMU (m/s^2)
302  Vector3f initAccVec;
303 
304  // TODO we should average accel readings over several cycles
305  initAccVec = _ahrs->get_ins().get_accel();
306 
307  // read the magnetometer data
308  readMagData();
309 
310  // normalise the acceleration vector
311  float pitch=0, roll=0;
312  if (initAccVec.length() > 0.001f) {
313  initAccVec.normalize();
314 
315  // calculate initial pitch angle
316  pitch = asinf(initAccVec.x);
317 
318  // calculate initial roll angle
319  roll = -asinf(initAccVec.y / cosf(pitch));
320  }
321 
322  // calculate initial orientation and earth magnetic field states
323  Quaternion initQuat;
324  initQuat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(roll, pitch);
325 
326  // check on ground status
327  SetFlightAndFusionModes();
328 
329  // write to state vector
330  state.quat = initQuat;
331  state.gyro_bias.zero();
332  state.accel_zbias1 = 0;
333  state.accel_zbias2 = 0;
334  state.wind_vel.zero();
335  state.body_magfield.zero();
336 
337  // read the GPS and set the position and velocity states
338  readGpsData();
339  ResetVelocity();
340  ResetPosition();
341 
342  // read the barometer and set the height state
343  readHgtData();
344  ResetHeight();
345 
346  // set stored states to current state
347  StoreStatesReset();
348 
349  // set to true now we have intialised the states
350  statesInitialised = true;
351 
352  // define Earth rotation vector in the NED navigation frame
353  calcEarthRateNED(earthRateNED, _ahrs->get_home().lat);
354 
355  // initialise IMU pre-processing states
356  readIMUData();
357 
358  // initialise the covariance matrix
359  CovarianceInit();
360 
361  return true;
362 }

364 // Update Filter States - this should be called whenever new IMU data is available
365 void NavEKF_core::UpdateFilter()
366 {
367  // zero the delta quaternion used by the strapdown navigation because it is published
368  // and we need to return a zero rotation of the INS fails to update it
369  correctedDelAngQuat.initialise();
370 
371  // don't run filter updates if states have not been initialised
372  if (!statesInitialised) {
373  return;
374  }
375 
376  // start the timer used for load measurement
377 #if EKF_DISABLE_INTERRUPTS
378  irqstate_t istate = irqsave();
379 #endif
380  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_UpdateFilter);
381 
382  //get starting time for update step
383  imuSampleTime_ms = hal.scheduler->millis();
384 
385  // read IMU data and convert to delta angles and velocities
386  readIMUData();
387 
388  static bool prev_armed = false;
389  bool armed = getVehicleArmStatus();
390 
391  // the vehicle was previously disarmed and time has slipped
392  // gyro auto-zero has likely just been done - skip this timestep
393  if (!prev_armed && dtDelAng > dtIMUavg*5.0f) {
394  // stop the timer used for load measurement
395  prev_armed = armed;
396  goto end;
397  }
398  prev_armed = armed;
399 
400  // detect if the filter update has been delayed for too long
401  if (dtDelAng > 0.2f) {
402  // we have stalled for too long - reset states
403  ResetVelocity();
404  ResetPosition();
405  ResetHeight();
406  StoreStatesReset();
407  //Initialise IMU pre-processing states
408  readIMUData();
409  // stop the timer used for load measurement
410  goto end;
411  }
412 
413  // check if on ground
414  SetFlightAndFusionModes();
415 
416  // Check arm status and perform required checks and mode changes
417  performArmingChecks();
418 
419  // run the strapdown INS equations every IMU update
420  UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED();
421 
422  // store the predicted states for subsequent use by measurement fusion
423  StoreStates();
424 
425  // sum delta angles and time used by covariance prediction
426  summedDelAng = summedDelAng + correctedDelAng;
427  summedDelVel = summedDelVel + correctedDelVel12;
428  dt += dtDelAng;
429 
430  // perform a covariance prediction if the total delta angle has exceeded the limit
431  // or the time limit will be exceeded at the next IMU update
432  if (((dt >= (covTimeStepMax - dtDelAng)) || (summedDelAng.length() > covDelAngMax))) {
433  CovariancePrediction();
434  } else {
435  covPredStep = false;
436  }
437 
438  // Read range finder data which is used by both position and optical flow fusion
439  readRangeFinder();
440 
441  // Update states using GPS, altimeter, compass, airspeed and synthetic sideslip observations
442  SelectVelPosFusion();
443  SelectMagFusion();
444  SelectFlowFusion();
445  SelectTasFusion();
446  SelectBetaFusion();
447 
448 end:
449  // stop the timer used for load measurement
450  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_UpdateFilter);
451 #if EKF_DISABLE_INTERRUPTS
452  irqrestore(istate);
453 #endif
454 }
455 
456 // select fusion of velocity, position and height measurements
457 void NavEKF_core::SelectVelPosFusion()
458 {
459  // check for and read new height data
460  readHgtData();
461 
462  // If we haven't received height data for a while, then declare the height data as being timed out
463  // set timeout period based on whether we have vertical GPS velocity available to constrain drift
464  hgtRetryTime = (useGpsVertVel && !velTimeout) ? hgtRetryTimeMode0 : hgtRetryTimeMode12;
465  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtMeasTime > hgtRetryTime) {
466  hgtTimeout = true;
467  }
468 
469  // command fusion of height data
470  if (newDataHgt)
471  {
472  // reset data arrived flag
473  newDataHgt = false;
474  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
475  memset(&hgtIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(hgtIncrStateDelta));
476  hgtUpdateCount = 0;
477  // enable fusion
478  fuseHgtData = true;
479  } else {
480  fuseHgtData = false;
481  }
482 
483  // check for and read new GPS data
484  readGpsData();
485 
486  // Specify which measurements should be used and check data for freshness
487  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
488 
489  // check if we can use opticalflow as a backup
490  bool optFlowBackup = (flowDataValid && !hgtTimeout);
491 
492  // Set GPS time-out threshold depending on whether we have an airspeed sensor to constrain drift
493  uint16_t gpsRetryTimeout = useAirspeed() ? gpsRetryTimeUseTAS : gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
494 
495  // Set the time that copters will fly without a GPS lock before failing the GPS and switching to a non GPS mode
496  uint16_t gpsFailTimeout = optFlowBackup ? gpsFailTimeWithFlow : gpsRetryTimeout;
497 
498  // If we haven't received GPS data for a while, then declare the position and velocity data as being timed out
499  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastFixTime_ms > gpsFailTimeout) {
500  posTimeout = true;
501  velTimeout = true;
502  // If this happens in flight and we don't have airspeed or sideslip assumption or optical flow to constrain drift, then go into constant position mode.
503  // Stay in that mode until the vehicle is re-armed.
504  // If we can do optical flow nav (valid flow data and hieght above ground estimate, then go into flow nav mode.
505  // Stay in that mode until the vehicle is dis-armed.
506  if (vehicleArmed && !useAirspeed() && !assume_zero_sideslip()) {
507  if (optFlowBackup) {
508  // we can do optical flow only nav
509  frontend._fusionModeGPS = 3;
510  PV_AidingMode = AID_RELATIVE;
511  constPosMode = false;
512  } else {
513  constPosMode = true;
514  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
515  posTimeout = true;
516  velTimeout = true;
517  // reset the velocity
518  ResetVelocity();
519  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position
520  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
521  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
522  // reset the position
523  ResetPosition();
524  }
525  // set the position and velocity timeouts to indicate we are not using GPS data
526  posTimeout = true;
527  velTimeout = true;
528  }
529  }
530 
531  // command fusion of GPS data and reset states as required
532  if (newDataGps && (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE)) {
533  // reset data arrived flag
534  newDataGps = false;
535  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
536  memset(&gpsIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(gpsIncrStateDelta));
537  gpsUpdateCount = 0;
538  // use both if GPS use is enabled
539  fuseVelData = true;
540  fusePosData = true;
541  // If a long time since last GPS update, then reset position and velocity and reset stored state history
542  if (imuSampleTime_ms - secondLastFixTime_ms > gpsRetryTimeout) {
543  ResetPosition();
544  ResetVelocity();
545  // record the fail time
546  lastPosFailTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
547  // Reset the normalised innovation to avoid false failing the bad position fusion test
548  posTestRatio = 0.0f;
549  }
550  } else {
551  fuseVelData = false;
552  fusePosData = false;
553  }
554  } else if (constPosMode && (fuseHgtData || ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastConstPosFuseTime_ms) > 200))) {
555  // In constant position mode use synthetic position and velocity measurements set to zero whenever we are fusing a height measurement
556  // If no height has been received for 200 msec, then fuse anyway so we have a guaranteed minimum aiding rate equivalent to GPS
557  // only fuse synthetic measurements when rate of change of velocity is less than 0.5g to reduce attitude errors due to launch acceleration
558  // do not use velocity fusion to reduce the effect of movement on attitude
559  if (!vehicleArmed) {
560  fuseVelData = true;
561  } else {
562  fuseVelData = false;
563  }
564  if (accNavMag < 4.9f) {
565  fusePosData = true;
566  } else {
567  fusePosData = false;
568  }
569  // record the fusion time - used to control fusion rate when there is no baro data
570  lastConstPosFuseTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
571  } else {
572  fuseVelData = false;
573  fusePosData = false;
574  }
575 
576  // perform fusion
577  if (fuseVelData || fusePosData || fuseHgtData) {
578  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
579  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
580  FuseVelPosNED();
581  }
582 
583  // Fuse corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 5 and 10Hz pulsing in the output
584  if (gpsUpdateCount < gpsUpdateCountMax) {
585  gpsUpdateCount ++;
586  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
587  states[i] += gpsIncrStateDelta[i];
588  }
589  }
590  if (hgtUpdateCount < hgtUpdateCountMax) {
591  hgtUpdateCount ++;
592  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
593  states[i] += hgtIncrStateDelta[i];
594  }
595  }
596 
597  // Detect and declare bad GPS aiding status for minimum 10 seconds if a GPS rejection occurs after
598  // rejection of GPS and reset to GPS position. This addresses failure case where errors cause ongoing rejection
599  // of GPS and severe loss of position accuracy.
600  uint32_t gpsRetryTime;
601  if (useAirspeed()) {
602  gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeUseTAS;
603  } else {
604  gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
605  }
606  if ((posTestRatio > 2.0f) && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosFailTime) < gpsRetryTime) && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosFailTime) > gpsRetryTime/2) && fusePosData) {
607  lastGpsAidBadTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
608  gpsAidingBad = true;
609  }
610  gpsAidingBad = gpsAidingBad && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsAidBadTime_ms) < 10000);
611 }
612 
613 // select fusion of magnetometer data
614 void NavEKF_core::SelectMagFusion()
615 {
616  // start performance timer
617  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_FuseMagnetometer);
618 
619  // check for and read new magnetometer measurements
620  readMagData();
621 
622  // If we are using the compass and the magnetometer has been unhealthy for too long we declare a timeout
623  if (magHealth) {
624  magTimeout = false;
625  lastHealthyMagTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
626  } else if ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastHealthyMagTime_ms) > magFailTimeLimit_ms && use_compass()) {
627  magTimeout = true;
628  }
629 
630  // determine if conditions are right to start a new fusion cycle
631  bool dataReady = statesInitialised && use_compass() && newDataMag;
632  if (dataReady) {
633  // Calculate change in angle since last magetoemter fusion - used to check if in-flight alignment can be performed
634  // Use a quaternion division to calcualte the delta quaternion between the rotation at the current and last time
635  Quaternion deltaQuat = state.quat / prevQuatMagReset;
636  prevQuatMagReset = state.quat;
637  // convert the quaternion to a rotation vector and find its length
638  Vector3f deltaRotVec;
639  deltaQuat.to_axis_angle(deltaRotVec);
640  float deltaRot = deltaRotVec.length();
641 
642  // Check if the magnetic field states should be reset
643  if (vehicleArmed && !firstMagYawInit && (state.position.z - posDownAtArming) < -1.5f && !assume_zero_sideslip() && deltaRot < 0.1745f) {
644  // Do the first in-air yaw and earth mag field initialisation when the vehicle has gained 1.5m of altitude after arming if it is a non-fly forward vehicle (vertical takeoff)
645  // This is done to prevent magnetic field distoration from steel roofs and adjacent structures causing bad earth field and initial yaw values
646  // Do not do this alignment if the vehicle is rotating rapidly as timing erors in the mag data will cause significant errors
647  Vector3f eulerAngles;
648  statesAtMagMeasTime.quat.to_euler(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y, eulerAngles.z);
649  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
650  firstMagYawInit = true;
651  } else if (vehicleArmed && !secondMagYawInit && (state.position.z - posDownAtArming) < -5.0f && !assume_zero_sideslip() && deltaRot < 0.1745f) {
652  // Do the second and final yaw and earth mag field initialisation when the vehicle has gained 5.0m of altitude after arming if it is a non-fly forward vehicle (vertical takeoff)
653  // This second and final correction is needed for flight from large metal structures where the magnetic field distortion can extend up to 5m
654  // Do not do this alignment if the vehicle is rotating rapidly as timing erors in the mag data will cause significant errors
655  Vector3f eulerAngles;
656  statesAtMagMeasTime.quat.to_euler(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y, eulerAngles.z);
657  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
658  secondMagYawInit = true;
659  }
660 
661  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
662  memset(&magIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(magIncrStateDelta));
663  magUpdateCount = 0;
664  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
665  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
666  // fuse the three magnetometer componenents sequentially
667  for (mag_state.obsIndex = 0; mag_state.obsIndex <= 2; mag_state.obsIndex++) FuseMagnetometer();
668  }
669 
670  // Fuse corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 10Hz pulsing in the output
671  if (magUpdateCount < magUpdateCountMax) {
672  magUpdateCount ++;
673  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
674  states[i] += magIncrStateDelta[i];
675  }
676  }
677 
678  // stop performance timer
679  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_FuseMagnetometer);
680 }
681 
682 // select fusion of optical flow measurements
683 void NavEKF_core::SelectFlowFusion()
684 {
685  // start performance timer
686  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_FuseOptFlow);
687  // Perform Data Checks
688  // Check if the optical flow data is still valid
689  flowDataValid = ((imuSampleTime_ms - flowValidMeaTime_ms) < 1000);
690  // Check if the optical flow sensor has timed out
691  bool flowSensorTimeout = ((imuSampleTime_ms - flowValidMeaTime_ms) > 5000);
692  // Check if the fusion has timed out (flow measurements have been rejected for too long)
693  bool flowFusionTimeout = ((imuSampleTime_ms - prevFlowFuseTime_ms) > 5000);
694  // check is the terrain offset estimate is still valid
695  gndOffsetValid = ((imuSampleTime_ms - gndHgtValidTime_ms) < 5000);
696  // Perform tilt check
697  bool tiltOK = (Tnb_flow.c.z > DCM33FlowMin);
698  // Constrain measurements to zero if we are using optical flow and are on the ground
699  if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3 && !takeOffDetected && vehicleArmed) {
700  flowRadXYcomp[0] = 0.0f;
701  flowRadXYcomp[1] = 0.0f;
702  flowRadXY[0] = 0.0f;
703  flowRadXY[1] = 0.0f;
704  omegaAcrossFlowTime.zero();
705  flowDataValid = true;
706  }
707  // If the flow measurements have been rejected for too long and we are relying on them, then revert to constant position mode
708  if ((flowSensorTimeout || flowFusionTimeout) && PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) {
709  constPosMode = true;
710  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
711  // reset the velocity
712  ResetVelocity();
713  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position
714  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
715  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
716  // reset the position
717  ResetPosition();
718  }
719  // if we do have valid flow measurements, fuse data into a 1-state EKF to estimate terrain height
720  // we don't do terrain height estimation in optical flow only mode as the ground becomes our zero height reference
721  if ((newDataFlow || newDataRng) && tiltOK) {
722  // fuse range data into the terrain estimator if available
723  fuseRngData = newDataRng;
724  // fuse optical flow data into the terrain estimator if available and if there is no range data (range data is better)
725  fuseOptFlowData = (newDataFlow && !fuseRngData);
726  // Estimate the terrain offset (runs a one state EKF)
727  EstimateTerrainOffset();
728  // Indicate we have used the range data
729  newDataRng = false;
730  // we don't do subsequent fusion of optical flow data into the main filter if GPS is good and terrain offset data is invalid
731  // because an invalid height above ground estimate will cause the optical flow measurements to fight the GPS
732  if (!gpsNotAvailable && !gndOffsetValid) {
733  // turn off fusion permissions
734  // reset the flags to indicate that no new range finder or flow data is available for fusion
735  newDataFlow = false;
736  }
737  }
738 
739  // Fuse optical flow data into the main filter
740  // if the filter is initialised, we have data to fuse and the vehicle is not excessively tilted, then perform optical flow fusion
741  if (flowDataValid && newDataFlow && tiltOK && !constPosMode)
742  {
743  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
744  memset(&flowIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(flowIncrStateDelta));
745  flowUpdateCount = 0;
746  // Set the flow noise used by the fusion processes
747  R_LOS = sq(max(frontend._flowNoise, 0.05f));
748  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
749  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
750  // Fuse the optical flow X and Y axis data into the main filter sequentially
751  for (flow_state.obsIndex = 0; flow_state.obsIndex <= 1; flow_state.obsIndex++) FuseOptFlow();
752  // reset flag to indicate that no new flow data is available for fusion
753  newDataFlow = false;
754  // indicate that flow fusion has been performed. This is used for load spreading.
755  flowFusePerformed = true;
756  }
757 
758  // Apply corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 10Hz pulsing in the output
759  if (flowUpdateCount < flowUpdateCountMax) {
760  flowUpdateCount ++;
761  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
762  states[i] += flowIncrStateDelta[i];
763  }
764  }
765  // stop the performance timer
766  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_FuseOptFlow);
767 }
768 
769 // select fusion of true airspeed measurements
770 void NavEKF_core::SelectTasFusion()
771 {
772  // get true airspeed measurement
773  readAirSpdData();
774 
775  // If we haven't received airspeed data for a while, then declare the airspeed data as being timed out
776  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastAirspeedUpdate > tasRetryTime) {
777  tasTimeout = true;
778  }
779 
780  // if the filter is initialised, wind states are not inhibited and we have data to fuse, then perform TAS fusion
781  tasDataWaiting = (statesInitialised && !inhibitWindStates && newDataTas);
782  if (tasDataWaiting)
783  {
784  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
785  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
786  FuseAirspeed();
787  TASmsecPrev = imuSampleTime_ms;
788  tasDataWaiting = false;
789  newDataTas = false;
790  }
791 }
792 
793 // select fusion of synthetic sideslip measurements
794 // synthetic sidelip fusion only works for fixed wing aircraft and relies on the average sideslip being close to zero
795 // it requires a stable wind for best results and should not be used for aerobatic flight with manoeuvres that induce large sidslip angles (eg knife-edge, spins, etc)
796 void NavEKF_core::SelectBetaFusion()
797 {
798  // set true when the fusion time interval has triggered
799  bool f_timeTrigger = ((imuSampleTime_ms - BETAmsecPrev) >= msecBetaAvg);
800  // set true when use of synthetic sideslip fusion is necessary because we have limited sensor data or are dead reckoning position
801  bool f_required = !(use_compass() && useAirspeed() && posHealth);
802  // set true when sideslip fusion is feasible (requires zero sideslip assumption to be valid and use of wind states)
803  bool f_feasible = (assume_zero_sideslip() && !inhibitWindStates);
804  // use synthetic sideslip fusion if feasible, required and enough time has lapsed since the last fusion
805  if (f_feasible && f_required && f_timeTrigger) {
806  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
807  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
808  FuseSideslip();
809  BETAmsecPrev = imuSampleTime_ms;
810  }
811 }
812 
813 // update the quaternion, velocity and position states using IMU measurements
814 void NavEKF_core::UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED()
815 {
816  Vector3f delVelNav; // delta velocity vector calculated using a blend of IMU1 and IMU2 data
817  Vector3f delVelNav1; // delta velocity vector calculated using IMU1 data
818  Vector3f delVelNav2; // delta velocity vector calculated using IMU2 data
819 
820  // remove sensor bias errors
821  correctedDelAng = dAngIMU - state.gyro_bias;
822  correctedDelVel1 = dVelIMU1;
823  correctedDelVel2 = dVelIMU2;
824  correctedDelVel1.z -= state.accel_zbias1;
825  correctedDelVel2.z -= state.accel_zbias2;
826 
827  // use weighted average of both IMU units for delta velocities
828  // Over-ride accelerometer blend weighting using a hard switch based on the IMU consistency and vibration monitoring checks
829  if (lastImuSwitchState == IMUSWITCH_IMU0) {
830  IMU1_weighting = 1.0f;
831  } else if (lastImuSwitchState == IMUSWITCH_IMU1) {
832  IMU1_weighting = 0.0f;
833  }
834  correctedDelVel12 = correctedDelVel1 * IMU1_weighting + correctedDelVel2 * (1.0f - IMU1_weighting);
835  float dtDelVel = dtDelVel1 * IMU1_weighting + dtDelVel2 * (1.0f - IMU1_weighting);
836 
837  // apply correction for earths rotation rate
838  // % * - and + operators have been overloaded
839  correctedDelAng = correctedDelAng - prevTnb * earthRateNED*dtDelAng;
840 
841  // convert the rotation vector to its equivalent quaternion
842  correctedDelAngQuat.from_axis_angle(correctedDelAng);
843 
844  // update the quaternion states by rotating from the previous attitude through
845  // the delta angle rotation quaternion and normalise
846  state.quat *= correctedDelAngQuat;
847  state.quat.normalize();
848 
849  // calculate the body to nav cosine matrix
850  Matrix3f Tbn_temp;
851  state.quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn_temp);
852  prevTnb = Tbn_temp.transposed();
853 
854  // calculate earth frame delta velocity due to gravity
855  float delVelGravity1_z = GRAVITY_MSS*dtDelVel1;
856  float delVelGravity2_z = GRAVITY_MSS*dtDelVel2;
857  float delVelGravity_z = delVelGravity1_z * IMU1_weighting + delVelGravity2_z * (1.0f - IMU1_weighting);
858 
859  // transform body delta velocities to delta velocities in the nav frame
860  // * and + operators have been overloaded
861 
862  // blended IMU calc
863  delVelNav = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel12;
864  delVelNav.z += delVelGravity_z;
865 
866  // single IMU calcs
867  delVelNav1 = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel1;
868  delVelNav1.z += delVelGravity1_z;
869 
870  delVelNav2 = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel2;
871  delVelNav2.z += delVelGravity2_z;
872 
873  // calculate the rate of change of velocity (used for launch detect and other functions)
874  velDotNED = delVelNav / dtDelVel;
875 
876  // apply a first order lowpass filter
877  velDotNEDfilt = velDotNED * 0.05f + velDotNEDfilt * 0.95f;
878 
879  // calculate a magnitude of the filtered nav acceleration (required for GPS
880  // variance estimation)
881  accNavMag = velDotNEDfilt.length();
882  accNavMagHoriz = pythagorous2(velDotNEDfilt.x , velDotNEDfilt.y);
883 
884  // save velocity for use in trapezoidal intergration for position calcuation
885  Vector3f lastVelocity = state.velocity;
886  Vector3f lastVel1 = state.vel1;
887  Vector3f lastVel2 = state.vel2;
888 
889  // sum delta velocities to get velocity
890  state.velocity += delVelNav;
891  state.vel1 += delVelNav1;
892  state.vel2 += delVelNav2;
893 
894  // apply a trapezoidal integration to velocities to calculate position
895  state.position += (state.velocity + lastVelocity) * (dtDelVel*0.5f);
896  state.posD1 += (state.vel1.z + lastVel1.z) * (dtDelVel1*0.5f);
897  state.posD2 += (state.vel2.z + lastVel2.z) * (dtDelVel2*0.5f);
898 
899  // capture current angular rate to augmented state vector for use by optical flow fusion
900  state.omega = correctedDelAng / dtDelAng;
901 
902  // LPF the yaw rate using a 1 second time constant yaw rate and determine if we are doing continual
903  // fast rotations that can cause problems due to gyro scale factor errors.
904  float alphaLPF = constrain_float(dtDelAng, 0.0f, 1.0f);
905  yawRateFilt += (state.omega.z - yawRateFilt)*alphaLPF;
906  if (fabsf(yawRateFilt) > 1.0f) {
907  highYawRate = true;
908  } else {
909  highYawRate = false;
910  }
911 
912  // limit states to protect against divergence
913  ConstrainStates();
914 
915  // update vertical velocity and position states used to provide a vertical position derivative output
916  // using a simple complementary filter
917  float lastPosDownDerivative = posDownDerivative;
918  posDownDerivative = 2.0f * (state.position.z - posDown);
919  posDown += (posDownDerivative + lastPosDownDerivative + 2.0f*delVelNav.z) * (dtDelVel*0.5f);
920 }
921 
922 // calculate the predicted state covariance matrix
923 void NavEKF_core::CovariancePrediction()
924 {
925  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_CovariancePrediction);
926  float windVelSigma; // wind velocity 1-sigma process noise - m/s
927  float dAngBiasSigma;// delta angle bias 1-sigma process noise - rad/s
928  float dVelBiasSigma;// delta velocity bias 1-sigma process noise - m/s
929  float magEarthSigma;// earth magnetic field 1-sigma process noise
930  float magBodySigma; // body magnetic field 1-sigma process noise
931  float daxCov; // X axis delta angle variance rad^2
932  float dayCov; // Y axis delta angle variance rad^2
933  float dazCov; // Z axis delta angle variance rad^2
934  float dvxCov; // X axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
935  float dvyCov; // Y axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
936  float dvzCov; // Z axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
937  float dvx; // X axis delta velocity (m/s)
938  float dvy; // Y axis delta velocity (m/s)
939  float dvz; // Z axis delta velocity (m/s)
940  float dax; // X axis delta angle (rad)
941  float day; // Y axis delta angle (rad)
942  float daz; // Z axis delta angle (rad)
943  float q0; // attitude quaternion
944  float q1; // attitude quaternion
945  float q2; // attitude quaternion
946  float q3; // attitude quaternion
947  float dax_b; // X axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
948  float day_b; // Y axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
949  float daz_b; // Z axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
950  float dvz_b; // Z axis delta velocity measurement bias (rad)
951 
952  // calculate covariance prediction process noise
953  // use filtered height rate to increase wind process noise when climbing or descending
954  // this allows for wind gradient effects.
955  // filter height rate using a 10 second time constant filter
956  float alpha = 0.1f * dt;
957  hgtRate = hgtRate * (1.0f - alpha) - state.velocity.z * alpha;
958 
959  // use filtered height rate to increase wind process noise when climbing or descending
960  // this allows for wind gradient effects.
961  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
962  windVelSigma = dt * constrain_float(frontend._windVelProcessNoise, 0.01f, 1.0f) * (1.0f + constrain_float(frontend._wndVarHgtRateScale, 0.0f, 1.0f) * fabsf(hgtRate));
963  } else {
964  windVelSigma = 0.0f;
965  }
966  dAngBiasSigma = dt * constrain_float(frontend._gyroBiasProcessNoise, 1e-7f, 1e-5f);
967  dVelBiasSigma = dt * constrain_float(frontend._accelBiasProcessNoise, 1e-5f, 1e-3f);
968  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
969  magEarthSigma = dt * constrain_float(frontend._magEarthProcessNoise, 1e-4f, 1e-2f);
970  magBodySigma = dt * constrain_float(frontend._magBodyProcessNoise, 1e-4f, 1e-2f);
971  } else {
972  magEarthSigma = 0.0f;
973  magBodySigma = 0.0f;
974  }
975  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=9; i++) processNoise[i] = 1.0e-9f;
976  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) processNoise[i] = dAngBiasSigma;
977  // scale gyro bias noise when disarmed to allow for faster bias estimation
978  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) {
979  processNoise[i] = dAngBiasSigma;
980  if (!vehicleArmed) {
981  processNoise[i] *= gyroBiasNoiseScaler;
982  }
983  }
984  // if we are yawing rapidly, inhibit yaw gyro bias learning to prevent gyro scale factor errors from corrupting the bias estimate
985  if (highYawRate) {
986  processNoise[12] = 0.0f;
987  P[12][12] = 0.0f;
988  }
989  // scale accel bias noise when disarmed to allow for faster bias estimation
990  // inhibit bias estimation during takeoff with ground effect to prevent bad bias learning
991  if (expectGndEffectTakeoff) {
992  processNoise[13] = 0.0f;
993  } else if (!vehicleArmed) {
994  processNoise[13] = dVelBiasSigma * accelBiasNoiseScaler;
995  } else {
996  processNoise[13] = dVelBiasSigma;
997  }
998  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) processNoise[i] = windVelSigma;
999  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) processNoise[i] = magEarthSigma;
1000  for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) processNoise[i] = magBodySigma;
1001  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) processNoise[i] = sq(processNoise[i]);
1002 
1003  // set variables used to calculate covariance growth
1004  dvx = summedDelVel.x;
1005  dvy = summedDelVel.y;
1006  dvz = summedDelVel.z;
1007  dax = summedDelAng.x;
1008  day = summedDelAng.y;
1009  daz = summedDelAng.z;
1010  q0 = state.quat[0];
1011  q1 = state.quat[1];
1012  q2 = state.quat[2];
1013  q3 = state.quat[3];
1014  dax_b = state.gyro_bias.x;
1015  day_b = state.gyro_bias.y;
1016  daz_b = state.gyro_bias.z;
1017  dvz_b = IMU1_weighting * state.accel_zbias1 + (1.0f - IMU1_weighting) * state.accel_zbias2;
1018  frontend._gyrNoise = constrain_float(frontend._gyrNoise, 1e-3f, 5e-2f);
1019  daxCov = sq(dt*frontend._gyrNoise);
1020  dayCov = sq(dt*frontend._gyrNoise);
1021  // Account for 3% scale factor error on Z angular rate. This reduces chance of continuous fast rotations causing loss of yaw reference.
1022  dazCov = sq(dt*frontend._gyrNoise) + sq(dt*0.03f*yawRateFilt);
1023  frontend._accNoise = constrain_float(frontend._accNoise, 5e-2f, 1.0f);
1024  dvxCov = sq(dt*frontend._accNoise);
1025  dvyCov = sq(dt*frontend._accNoise);
1026  dvzCov = sq(dt*frontend._accNoise);
1027 
1028  // calculate the predicted covariance due to inertial sensor error propagation
1029  SF[0] = dvz - dvz_b;
1030  SF[1] = 2*q3*SF[0] + 2*dvx*q1 + 2*dvy*q2;
1031  SF[2] = 2*dvx*q3 - 2*q1*SF[0] + 2*dvy*q0;
1032  SF[3] = 2*q2*SF[0] + 2*dvx*q0 - 2*dvy*q3;
1033  SF[4] = day/2 - day_b/2;
1034  SF[5] = daz/2 - daz_b/2;
1035  SF[6] = dax/2 - dax_b/2;
1036  SF[7] = dax_b/2 - dax/2;
1037  SF[8] = daz_b/2 - daz/2;
1038  SF[9] = day_b/2 - day/2;
1039  SF[10] = 2*q0*SF[0];
1040  SF[11] = q1/2;
1041  SF[12] = q2/2;
1042  SF[13] = q3/2;
1043  SF[14] = 2*dvy*q1;
1044 
1045  SG[0] = q0/2;
1046  SG[1] = sq(q3);
1047  SG[2] = sq(q2);
1048  SG[3] = sq(q1);
1049  SG[4] = sq(q0);
1050  SG[5] = 2*q2*q3;
1051  SG[6] = 2*q1*q3;
1052  SG[7] = 2*q1*q2;
1053 
1054  SQ[0] = dvzCov*(SG[5] - 2*q0*q1)*(SG[1] - SG[2] - SG[3] + SG[4]) - dvyCov*(SG[5] + 2*q0*q1)*(SG[1] - SG[2] + SG[3] - SG[4]) + dvxCov*(SG[6] - 2*q0*q2)*(SG[7] + 2*q0*q3);

1537  nextP[21][0] = P[21][0] + P[21][1]*SF[7] + P[21][2]*SF[9] + P[21][3]*SF[8] + P[21][10]*SF[11] + P[21][11]*SPP[7] + P[21][12]*SPP[6];
1538  nextP[21][1] = P[21][1] + P[21][0]*SF[6] + P[21][2]*SF[5] + P[21][3]*SF[9] + P[21][11]*SPP[6] - P[21][12]*SPP[7] - (P[21][10]*q0)/2;
1539  nextP[21][2] = P[21][2] + P[21][0]*SF[4] + P[21][1]*SF[8] + P[21][3]*SF[6] + P[21][12]*SF[11] - P[21][10]*SPP[6] - (P[21][11]*q0)/2;
1540  nextP[21][3] = P[21][3] + P[21][0]*SF[5] + P[21][1]*SF[4] + P[21][2]*SF[7] - P[21][11]*SF[11] + P[21][10]*SPP[7] - (P[21][12]*q0)/2;
1541  nextP[21][4] = P[21][4] + P[21][1]*SF[1] + P[21][0]*SF[3] + P[21][2]*SPP[0] - P[21][3]*SPP[2] - P[21][13]*SPP[4];
1542  nextP[21][5] = P[21][5] + P[21][0]*SF[2] + P[21][2]*SF[1] + P[21][3]*SF[3] - P[21][1]*SPP[0] + P[21][13]*SPP[3];
1543  nextP[21][6] = P[21][6] + P[21][1]*SF[2] + P[21][3]*SF[1] + P[21][0]*SPP[0] - P[21][2]*SPP[1] - P[21][13]*SPP[5];
1544  nextP[21][7] = P[21][7] + P[21][4]*dt;
1545  nextP[21][8] = P[21][8] + P[21][5]*dt;
1546  nextP[21][9] = P[21][9] + P[21][6]*dt;
1547  nextP[21][10] = P[21][10];
1548  nextP[21][11] = P[21][11];
1549  nextP[21][12] = P[21][12];
1550  nextP[21][13] = P[21][13];
1551  nextP[21][14] = P[21][14];
1552  nextP[21][15] = P[21][15];
1553  nextP[21][16] = P[21][16];
1554  nextP[21][17] = P[21][17];
1555  nextP[21][18] = P[21][18];
1556  nextP[21][19] = P[21][19];
1557  nextP[21][20] = P[21][20];
1558  nextP[21][21] = P[21][21];
1559 
1560  // add the general state process noise variances
1561  for (uint8_t i=0; i<= 21; i++)
1562  {
1563  nextP[i][i] = nextP[i][i] + processNoise[i];
1564  }
1565 
1566  // if the total position variance exceeds 1e4 (100m), then stop covariance
1567  // growth by setting the predicted to the previous values
1568  // This prevent an ill conditioned matrix from occurring for long periods
1569  // without GPS
1570  if ((P[7][7] + P[8][8]) > 1e4f)
1571  {
1572  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++)
1573  {
1574  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
1575  {
1576  nextP[i][j] = P[i][j];
1577  nextP[j][i] = P[j][i];
1578  }
1579  }
1580  }
1581 
1582  // copy covariances to output and fix numerical errors
1583  CopyAndFixCovariances();
1584 
1585  // constrain diagonals to prevent ill-conditioning
1586  ConstrainVariances();
1587 
1588  // set the flag to indicate that covariance prediction has been performed and reset the increments used by the covariance prediction
1589  covPredStep = true;
1590  summedDelAng.zero();
1591  summedDelVel.zero();
1592  dt = 0.0f;
1593 
1594  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_CovariancePrediction);
1595 }
1596 
1597 // fuse selected position, velocity and height measurements
1598 void NavEKF_core::FuseVelPosNED()
1599 {
1600  // start performance timer
1601  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_FuseVelPosNED);
1602 
1603  // health is set bad until test passed
1604  velHealth = false;
1605  posHealth = false;
1606  hgtHealth = false;
1607 
1608  // declare variables used to check measurement errors
1609  Vector3f velInnov;
1610  Vector3f velInnov1;
1611  Vector3f velInnov2;
1612 
1613  // declare variables used to control access to arrays
1614  bool fuseData[6] = {false,false,false,false,false,false};
1615  uint8_t stateIndex;
1616  uint8_t obsIndex;
1617 
1618  // declare variables used by state and covariance update calculations
1619  float posErr;
1620  Vector6 R_OBS; // Measurement variances used for fusion
1621  Vector6 R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS; // Measurement variances used for data checks only
1622  Vector6 observation;
1623  float SK;
1624 
1625  // perform sequential fusion of GPS measurements. This assumes that the
1626  // errors in the different velocity and position components are
1627  // uncorrelated which is not true, however in the absence of covariance
1628  // data from the GPS receiver it is the only assumption we can make
1629  // so we might as well take advantage of the computational efficiencies
1630  // associated with sequential fusion
1631  if (fuseVelData || fusePosData || fuseHgtData) {
1632 
1633  // if constant position mode use the current states to calculate the predicted
1634  // measurement rather than use states from a previous time. We need to do this
1635  // because there may be no stored states due to lack of real measurements.
1636  if (constPosMode) {
1637  statesAtPosTime = state;
1638  }
1639 
1640  // set the GPS data timeout depending on whether airspeed data is present
1641  uint32_t gpsRetryTime;
1642  if (useAirspeed()) gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeUseTAS;
1643  else gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
1644 
1645  // form the observation vector and zero velocity and horizontal position observations if in constant position mode
1646  if (!constPosMode) {
1647  observation[0] = velNED.x;
1648  observation[1] = velNED.y;
1649  observation[2] = velNED.z;
1650  observation[3] = gpsPosNE.x;
1651  observation[4] = gpsPosNE.y;
1652  } else if (constPosMode){
1653  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=4; i++) observation[i] = 0.0f;
1654  }
1655  observation[5] = -hgtMea;
1656 
1657  // calculate additional error in GPS position caused by manoeuvring
1658  posErr = gpsPosVarAccScale * accNavMag;
1659 
1660  // estimate the GPS Velocity, GPS horiz position and height measurement variances.
1661  // if the GPS is able to report a speed error, we use it to adjust the observation noise for GPS velocity
1662  // otherwise we scale it using manoeuvre acceleration
1663  if (gpsSpdAccuracy > 0.0f) {
1664  // use GPS receivers reported speed accuracy - floor at value set by gps noise parameter
1665  R_OBS[0] = sq(constrain_float(gpsSpdAccuracy, frontend._gpsHorizVelNoise, 50.0f));
1666  R_OBS[2] = sq(constrain_float(gpsSpdAccuracy, frontend._gpsVertVelNoise, 50.0f));
1667  } else {
1668  // calculate additional error in GPS velocity caused by manoeuvring
1669  R_OBS[0] = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsNEVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1670  R_OBS[2] = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsVertVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsDVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1671  }
1672  R_OBS[1] = R_OBS[0];
1673  R_OBS[3] = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsHorizPosNoise, 0.1f, 10.0f)) + sq(posErr);
1674  R_OBS[4] = R_OBS[3];
1675  R_OBS[5] = sq(constrain_float(frontend._baroAltNoise, 0.1f, 10.0f));
1676 
1677  // reduce weighting (increase observation noise) on baro if we are likely to be in ground effect
1678  if ((getTakeoffExpected() || getTouchdownExpected()) && vehicleArmed) {
1679  R_OBS[5] *= gndEffectBaroScaler;
1680  }
1681 
1682  // For data integrity checks we use the same measurement variances as used to calculate the Kalman gains for all measurements except GPS horizontal velocity
1683  // For horizontal GPs velocity we don't want the acceptance radius to increase with reported GPS accuracy so we use a value based on best GPs perfomrance
1684  // plus a margin for manoeuvres. It is better to reject GPS horizontal velocity errors early
1685  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=1; i++) R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i] = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsNEVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1686  for (uint8_t i=2; i<=5; i++) R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i] = R_OBS[i];
1687 
1688 
1689  // if vertical GPS velocity data is being used, check to see if the GPS vertical velocity and barometer
1690  // innovations have the same sign and are outside limits. If so, then it is likely aliasing is affecting
1691  // the accelerometers and we should disable the GPS and barometer innovation consistency checks.
1692  if (useGpsVertVel && fuseVelData && (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtMeasTime) < (2 * msecHgtAvg)) {
1693  // calculate innovations for height and vertical GPS vel measurements
1694  float hgtErr = statesAtHgtTime.position.z - observation[5];
1695  float velDErr = statesAtVelTime.velocity.z - observation[2];
1696  // check if they are the same sign and both more than 3-sigma out of bounds
1697  if ((hgtErr*velDErr > 0.0f) && (sq(hgtErr) > 9.0f * (P[9][9] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[5])) && (sq(velDErr) > 9.0f * (P[6][6] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[2]))) {
1698  badIMUdata = true;
1699  } else {
1700  badIMUdata = false;
1701  }
1702  }
1703 
1704  // calculate innovations and check GPS data validity using an innovation consistency check
1705  // test position measurements
1706  if (fusePosData) {
1707  // test horizontal position measurements
1708  innovVelPos[3] = statesAtPosTime.position.x - observation[3];
1709  innovVelPos[4] = statesAtPosTime.position.y - observation[4];
1710  varInnovVelPos[3] = P[7][7] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[3];
1711  varInnovVelPos[4] = P[8][8] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[4];
1712  // apply an innovation consistency threshold test, but don't fail if bad IMU data
1713  // calculate max valid position innovation squared based on a maximum horizontal inertial nav accel error and GPS noise parameter
1714  // max inertial nav error is scaled with horizontal g to allow for increased errors when manoeuvring
1715  float accelScale = (1.0f + 0.1f * accNavMag);
1716  float maxPosInnov2 = sq(frontend._gpsPosInnovGate * frontend._gpsHorizPosNoise) + sq(0.005f * accelScale * float(frontend._gpsGlitchAccelMax) * sq(0.001f * float(imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime)));
1717  posTestRatio = (sq(innovVelPos[3]) + sq(innovVelPos[4])) / maxPosInnov2;
1718  posHealth = ((posTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
1719  // declare a timeout condition if we have been too long without data or not aiding
1720  posTimeout = (((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime) > gpsRetryTime) || PV_AidingMode == AID_NONE);
1721  // use position data if healthy, timed out, or in constant position mode
1722  if (posHealth || posTimeout || constPosMode) {
1723  posHealth = true;
1724  // only reset the failed time and do glitch timeout checks if we are doing full aiding
1725  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
1726  lastPosPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
1727  // if timed out or outside the specified glitch radius, reset to the GPS position
1728  if (posTimeout || (maxPosInnov2 > sq(float(frontend._gpsGlitchRadiusMax)))) {
1729  // reset the position to the current GPS position
1730  ResetPosition();
1731  // reset the velocity to the GPS velocity
1732  ResetVelocity();
1733  // don't fuse data on this time step
1734  fusePosData = false;
1735  // record the fail time
1736  lastPosFailTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
1737  // Reset the normalised innovation to avoid false failing the bad position fusion test
1738  posTestRatio = 0.0f;
1739  }
1740  }
1741  } else {
1742  posHealth = false;
1743  }
1744  }
1745 
1746  // test velocity measurements
1747  if (fuseVelData) {
1748  // test velocity measurements
1749  uint8_t imax = 2;
1750  if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 1) {
1751  imax = 1;
1752  }
1753  float K1 = 0; // innovation to error ratio for IMU1
1754  float K2 = 0; // innovation to error ratio for IMU2
1755  float innovVelSumSq = 0; // sum of squares of velocity innovations
1756  float varVelSum = 0; // sum of velocity innovation variances
1757  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=imax; i++) {
1758  // velocity states start at index 4
1759  stateIndex = i + 4;
1760  // calculate innovations using blended and single IMU predicted states
1761  velInnov[i] = statesAtVelTime.velocity[i] - observation[i]; // blended
1762  velInnov1[i] = statesAtVelTime.vel1[i] - observation[i]; // IMU1
1763  velInnov2[i] = statesAtVelTime.vel2[i] - observation[i]; // IMU2
1764  // calculate innovation variance
1765  varInnovVelPos[i] = P[stateIndex][stateIndex] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i];
1766  // calculate error weightings for single IMU velocity states using
1767  // observation error to normalise
1768  float R_hgt;
1769  if (i == 2) {
1770  R_hgt = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsVertVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f));
1771  } else {
1772  R_hgt = sq(constrain_float(frontend._gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f));
1773  }
1774  K1 += R_hgt / (R_hgt + sq(velInnov1[i]));
1775  K2 += R_hgt / (R_hgt + sq(velInnov2[i]));
1776  // sum the innovation and innovation variances
1777  innovVelSumSq += sq(velInnov[i]);
1778  varVelSum += varInnovVelPos[i];
1779  }
1780  // calculate weighting used by fuseVelPosNED to do IMU accel data blending
1781  // this is used to detect and compensate for aliasing errors with the accelerometers
1782  // provide for a first order lowpass filter to reduce noise on the weighting if required
1783  // set weighting to 0.5 when on ground to allow more rapid learning of bias errors without 'ringing' in bias estimates
1784  // NOTE: this weighting can be overwritten in UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED
1785  if (vehicleArmed) {
1786  IMU1_weighting = 1.0f * (K1 / (K1 + K2)) + 0.0f * IMU1_weighting; // filter currently inactive
1787  } else {
1788  IMU1_weighting = 0.5f;
1789  }
1790  // apply an innovation consistency threshold test, but don't fail if bad IMU data
1791  // calculate the test ratio
1792  velTestRatio = innovVelSumSq / (varVelSum * sq(frontend._gpsVelInnovGate));
1793  // fail if the ratio is greater than 1
1794  velHealth = ((velTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
1795  // declare a timeout if we have not fused velocity data for too long or not aiding
1796  velTimeout = (((imuSampleTime_ms - lastVelPassTime) > gpsRetryTime) || PV_AidingMode == AID_NONE);
1797  // if data is healthy we fuse it
1798  if (velHealth || velTimeout) {
1799  velHealth = true;
1800  // restart the timeout count
1801  lastVelPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
1802  } else if (velTimeout && !posHealth && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
1803  // if data is not healthy and timed out and position is unhealthy and we are using aiding, we reset the velocity, but do not fuse data on this time step
1804  ResetVelocity();
1805  fuseVelData = false;
1806  } else {
1807  // if data is unhealthy and position is healthy, we do not fuse it
1808  velHealth = false;
1809  }
1810  }
1811 
1812  // test height measurements
1813  if (fuseHgtData) {
1814  // calculate height innovations
1815  innovVelPos[5] = statesAtHgtTime.position.z - observation[5];
1816  // calculate the innovation variance
1817  varInnovVelPos[5] = P[9][9] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[5];
1818  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
1819  hgtTestRatio = sq(innovVelPos[5]) / (sq(frontend._hgtInnovGate) * varInnovVelPos[5]);
1820  // fail if the ratio is > 1, but don't fail if bad IMU data
1821  hgtHealth = ((hgtTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
1822  hgtTimeout = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtPassTime_ms) > hgtRetryTime;
1823  // Fuse height data if healthy
1824  // Force a reset if timed out to prevent the possibility of inertial errors causing persistent loss of height reference
1825  // Force fusion in constant position mode on the ground to allow large accelerometer biases to be learned without rejecting barometer
1826  if (hgtHealth || hgtTimeout || (constPosMode && !vehicleArmed)) {
1827  // Calculate a filtered value to be used by pre-flight health checks
1828  // We need to filter because wind gusts can generate significant baro noise and we want to be able to detect bias errors in the inertial solution
1829  if (!vehicleArmed) {
1830  float dtBaro = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtPassTime_ms)*1.0e-3f;
1831  const float hgtInnovFiltTC = 2.0f;
1832  float alpha = constrain_float(dtBaro/(dtBaro+hgtInnovFiltTC),0.0f,1.0f);
1833  hgtInnovFiltState += (innovVelPos[5]-hgtInnovFiltState)*alpha;
1834  }
1835  // declare height healthy and able to be fused
1836  lastHgtPassTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
1837  hgtHealth = true;
1838  // if timed out, reset the height, but do not fuse data on this time step
1839  if (hgtTimeout) {
1840  ResetHeight();
1841  fuseHgtData = false;
1842  }
1843  }
1844  else {
1845  hgtHealth = false;
1846  }
1847  }
1848 
1849  // set range for sequential fusion of velocity and position measurements depending on which data is available and its health
1850  if (fuseVelData && useGpsVertVel && velHealth && !constPosMode && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
1851  fuseData[0] = true;
1852  fuseData[1] = true;
1853  fuseData[2] = true;
1854  }
1855  if (fuseVelData && frontend._fusionModeGPS == 1 && velHealth && !constPosMode && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
1856  fuseData[0] = true;
1857  fuseData[1] = true;
1858  }
1859  if ((fusePosData && posHealth && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) || constPosMode) {
1860  fuseData[3] = true;
1861  fuseData[4] = true;
1862  }
1863  if ((fuseHgtData && hgtHealth) || constPosMode) {
1864  fuseData[5] = true;
1865  }
1866 
1867  // fuse measurements sequentially
1868  for (obsIndex=0; obsIndex<=5; obsIndex++) {
1869  if (fuseData[obsIndex]) {
1870  stateIndex = 4 + obsIndex;
1871  // calculate the measurement innovation, using states from a different time coordinate if fusing height data
1872  // adjust scaling on GPS measurement noise variances if not enough satellites
1873  if (obsIndex <= 2)
1874  {
1875  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtVelTime.velocity[obsIndex] - observation[obsIndex];
1876  R_OBS[obsIndex] *= sq(gpsNoiseScaler);
1877  }
1878  else if (obsIndex == 3 || obsIndex == 4) {
1879  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtPosTime.position[obsIndex-3] - observation[obsIndex];
1880  R_OBS[obsIndex] *= sq(gpsNoiseScaler);
1881  } else {
1882  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtHgtTime.position[obsIndex-3] - observation[obsIndex];
1883  if (obsIndex == 5) {
1884  static const float gndMaxBaroErr = 4.0f;
1885  static const float gndBaroInnovFloor = -0.5f;
1886 
1887  if(getTouchdownExpected()) {
1888  // when a touchdown is expected, floor the barometer innovation at gndBaroInnovFloor
1889  // constrain the correction between 0 and gndBaroInnovFloor+gndMaxBaroErr
1890  // this function looks like this:
1891  // |/
1892  //---------|---------
1893  // ____/|
1894  // / |
1895  // / |
1896  innovVelPos[5] += constrain_float(-innovVelPos[5]+gndBaroInnovFloor, 0.0f, gndBaroInnovFloor+gndMaxBaroErr);
1897  }
1898  }
1899  }
1900 
1901  // calculate the Kalman gain and calculate innovation variances
1902  varInnovVelPos[obsIndex] = P[stateIndex][stateIndex] + R_OBS[obsIndex];
1903  SK = 1.0f/varInnovVelPos[obsIndex];
1904  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=12; i++) {
1905  Kfusion[i] = P[i][stateIndex]*SK;
1906  }
1907  // Only height and height rate observations are used to update z accel bias estimate
1908  // Protect Kalman gain from ill-conditioning
1909  // Don't update Z accel bias if off-level by greater than 60 degrees to avoid scale factor error effects
1910  // Don't update if we are taking off with ground effect
1911  if ((obsIndex == 5 || obsIndex == 2) && prevTnb.c.z > 0.5f && !getTakeoffExpected()) {
1912  Kfusion[13] = constrain_float(P[13][stateIndex]*SK,-1.0f,0.0f);
1913  } else {
1914  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;
1915  }
1916  // inhibit wind state estimation by setting Kalman gains to zero
1917  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
1918  Kfusion[14] = P[14][stateIndex]*SK;
1919  Kfusion[15] = P[15][stateIndex]*SK;
1920  } else {
1921  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
1922  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
1923  }
1924  // inhibit magnetic field state estimation by setting Kalman gains to zero
1925  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
1926  for (uint8_t i = 16; i<=21; i++) {
1927  Kfusion[i] = P[i][stateIndex]*SK;
1928  }
1929  } else {
1930  for (uint8_t i = 16; i<=21; i++) {
1931  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
1932  }
1933  }
1934 
1935  // Set the Kalman gain values for the single IMU states
1936  Kfusion[26] = Kfusion[9]; // IMU1 posD
1937  Kfusion[30] = Kfusion[9]; // IMU2 posD
1938  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=2; i++) {
1939  Kfusion[i+23] = Kfusion[i+4]; // IMU1 velNED
1940  Kfusion[i+27] = Kfusion[i+4]; // IMU2 velNED
1941  }
1942  // Don't update Z accel bias values for an acceleraometer we have hard switched away from
1943  if ((IMU1_weighting >= 0.1f) && (IMU1_weighting <= 0.9f)) {
1944  // both IMU's OK
1945  Kfusion[22] = Kfusion[13];
1946  } else if (IMU1_weighting < 0.1f) {
1947  // IMU1 bad
1948  Kfusion[22] = Kfusion[13];
1949  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;
1950  } else {
1951  // IMU2 bad
1952  Kfusion[22] = 0.0f;
1953  }
1954 
1955  // Correct states that have been predicted using single (not blended) IMU data
1956  if (obsIndex == 5){
1957  // Calculate height measurement innovations using single IMU states
1958  float hgtInnov1 = statesAtHgtTime.posD1 - observation[obsIndex];
1959  float hgtInnov2 = statesAtHgtTime.posD2 - observation[obsIndex];
1960 
1961  if (vehicleArmed) {
1962  // Correct single IMU prediction states using height measurement, limiting rate of change of bias to 0.005 m/s3
1963  float correctionLimit = 0.005f * dtIMUavg * dtVelPos;
1964  state.accel_zbias1 -= constrain_float(Kfusion[13] * hgtInnov1, -correctionLimit, correctionLimit); // IMU1 Z accel bias
1965  state.accel_zbias2 -= constrain_float(Kfusion[22] * hgtInnov2, -correctionLimit, correctionLimit); // IMU2 Z accel bias
1966  } else {
1967  // When disarmed, do not rate limit accel bias learning
1968  state.accel_zbias1 -= Kfusion[13] * hgtInnov1; // IMU1 Z accel bias
1969  state.accel_zbias2 -= Kfusion[22] * hgtInnov2; // IMU2 Z accel bias
1970  }
1971 
1972  for (uint8_t i = 23; i<=26; i++) {
1973  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * hgtInnov1; // IMU1 velNED,posD
1974  }
1975  for (uint8_t i = 27; i<=30; i++) {
1976  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * hgtInnov2; // IMU2 velNED,posD
1977  }
1978  } else if (obsIndex == 0 || obsIndex == 1 || obsIndex == 2) {
1979  // Correct single IMU prediction states using velocity measurements
1980  for (uint8_t i = 23; i<=26; i++) {
1981  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * velInnov1[obsIndex]; // IMU1 velNED,posD
1982  }
1983  for (uint8_t i = 27; i<=30; i++) {
1984  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * velInnov2[obsIndex]; // IMU2 velNED,posD
1985  }
1986  }
1987 
1988  // calculate state corrections and re-normalise the quaternions for states predicted using the blended IMU data
1989  // attitude, velocity and position corrections are spread across multiple prediction cycles between now
1990  // and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
1991  // Don't spread quaternion corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
1992  // Don't apply corrections to Z bias state as this has been done already as part of the single IMU calculations
1993  bool highRates = ((gpsUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
1994  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
1995  if (i != 13) {
1996  if ((i <= 3 && highRates) || i >= 10 || constPosMode) {
1997  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex];
1998  } else {
1999  if (obsIndex == 5) {
2000  hgtIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex] * hgtUpdateCountMaxInv;
2001  } else {
2002  gpsIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex] * gpsUpdateCountMaxInv;
2003  }
2004  }
2005  }
2006  }
2007  state.quat.normalize();
2008 
2009  // update the covariance - take advantage of direct observation of a single state at index = stateIndex to reduce computations
2010  // this is a numerically optimised implementation of standard equation P = (I - K*H)*P;
2011  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) {
2012  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++)
2013  {
2014  KHP[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * P[stateIndex][j];
2015  }
2016  }
2017  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) {
2018  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++) {
2019  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
2020  }
2021  }
2022  }
2023  }
2024  }
2025 
2026  // force the covariance matrix to be symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
2027  ForceSymmetry();
2028  ConstrainVariances();
2029 
2030  // stop performance timer
2031  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_FuseVelPosNED);
2032 }
2033 
2034 // fuse magnetometer measurements and apply innovation consistency checks
2035 // fuse each axis on consecutive time steps to spread computional load
2036 void NavEKF_core::FuseMagnetometer()
2037 {
2038  // declarations
2039  ftype &q0 = mag_state.q0;
2040  ftype &q1 = mag_state.q1;
2041  ftype &q2 = mag_state.q2;
2042  ftype &q3 = mag_state.q3;
2043  ftype &magN = mag_state.magN;
2044  ftype &magE = mag_state.magE;
2045  ftype &magD = mag_state.magD;
2046  ftype &magXbias = mag_state.magXbias;
2047  ftype &magYbias = mag_state.magYbias;
2048  ftype &magZbias = mag_state.magZbias;
2049  uint8_t &obsIndex = mag_state.obsIndex;
2050  Matrix3f &DCM = mag_state.DCM;
2051  Vector3f &MagPred = mag_state.MagPred;
2052  ftype &R_MAG = mag_state.R_MAG;
2053  ftype *SH_MAG = &mag_state.SH_MAG[0];
2054  Vector22 H_MAG;
2055  Vector6 SK_MX;
2056  Vector6 SK_MY;
2057  Vector6 SK_MZ;
2058 
2059  // perform sequential fusion of magnetometer measurements.
2060  // this assumes that the errors in the different components are
2061  // uncorrelated which is not true, however in the absence of covariance
2062  // data fit is the only assumption we can make
2063  // so we might as well take advantage of the computational efficiencies
2064  // associated with sequential fusion
2065  // calculate observation jacobians and Kalman gains
2066  if (obsIndex == 0)
2067  {
2068  // copy required states to local variable names
2069  q0 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[0];
2070  q1 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[1];
2071  q2 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[2];
2072  q3 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[3];
2073  magN = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[0];
2074  magE = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[1];
2075  magD = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[2];
2076  magXbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[0];
2077  magYbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[1];
2078  magZbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[2];
2079 
2080  // rotate predicted earth components into body axes and calculate
2081  // predicted measurements
2082  DCM[0][0] = q0*q0 + q1*q1 - q2*q2 - q3*q3;
2083  DCM[0][1] = 2*(q1*q2 + q0*q3);
2084  DCM[0][2] = 2*(q1*q3-q0*q2);
2085  DCM[1][0] = 2*(q1*q2 - q0*q3);
2086  DCM[1][1] = q0*q0 - q1*q1 + q2*q2 - q3*q3;
2087  DCM[1][2] = 2*(q2*q3 + q0*q1);
2088  DCM[2][0] = 2*(q1*q3 + q0*q2);
2089  DCM[2][1] = 2*(q2*q3 - q0*q1);
2090  DCM[2][2] = q0*q0 - q1*q1 - q2*q2 + q3*q3;
2091  MagPred[0] = DCM[0][0]*magN + DCM[0][1]*magE + DCM[0][2]*magD + magXbias;
2092  MagPred[1] = DCM[1][0]*magN + DCM[1][1]*magE + DCM[1][2]*magD + magYbias;
2093  MagPred[2] = DCM[2][0]*magN + DCM[2][1]*magE + DCM[2][2]*magD + magZbias;
2094 
2095  // scale magnetometer observation error with total angular rate
2096  R_MAG = sq(constrain_float(frontend._magNoise, 0.01f, 0.5f)) + sq(magVarRateScale*dAngIMU.length() / dtIMUavg);
2097 
2098  // calculate observation jacobians
2099  SH_MAG[0] = 2*magD*q3 + 2*magE*q2 + 2*magN*q1;
2100  SH_MAG[1] = 2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2;
2101  SH_MAG[2] = 2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3;
2102  SH_MAG[3] = sq(q3);
2103  SH_MAG[4] = sq(q2);
2104  SH_MAG[5] = sq(q1);
2105  SH_MAG[6] = sq(q0);
2106  SH_MAG[7] = 2*magN*q0;
2107  SH_MAG[8] = 2*magE*q3;
2108  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_MAG[i] = 0;
2109  H_MAG[0] = SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2;
2110  H_MAG[1] = SH_MAG[0];
2111  H_MAG[2] = 2*magE*q1 - 2*magD*q0 - 2*magN*q2;
2112  H_MAG[3] = SH_MAG[2];
2113  H_MAG[16] = SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[6];
2114  H_MAG[17] = 2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2;
2115  H_MAG[18] = 2*q1*q3 - 2*q0*q2;
2116  H_MAG[19] = 1;
2117 
2118  // calculate Kalman gain
2119  float temp = (P[19][19] + R_MAG + P[1][19]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][19]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][19]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) - (2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2)*(P[19][2] + P[1][2]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][2]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][2]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][2]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][2]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][2]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][2]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + (SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)*(P[19][0] + P[1][0]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][0]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][0]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][0]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][0]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][0]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][0]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[0]*(P[19][1] + P[1][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][1]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][1]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][1]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][1]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][1]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][1]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[2]*(P[19][3] + P[1][3]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][3]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][3]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][3]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][3]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) - (SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6])*(P[19][16] + P[1][16]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][16]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][16]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][16]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][16]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][16]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][16]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + P[17][19]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][19]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][19]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + (2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2)*(P[19][17] + P[1][17]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][17]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][17]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][17]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][17]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][17]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][17]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) - (2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3)*(P[19][18] + P[1][18]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][18]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][18]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][18]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][18]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][18]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][18]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + P[0][19]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2));
2120  if (temp >= R_MAG) {
2121  SK_MX[0] = 1.0f / temp;
2122  faultStatus.bad_xmag = false;
2123  } else {
2124  // the calculation is badly conditioned, so we cannot perform fusion on this step
2125  // we reset the covariance matrix and try again next measurement
2126  CovarianceInit();
2127  obsIndex = 1;
2128  faultStatus.bad_xmag = true;
2129  return;
2130  }
2131  SK_MX[1] = SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6];
2132  SK_MX[2] = 2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2;
2133  SK_MX[3] = SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2;
2134  SK_MX[4] = 2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3;
2135  SK_MX[5] = 2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2;
2136  Kfusion[0] = SK_MX[0]*(P[0][19] + P[0][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[0][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[0][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[0][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[0][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[0][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[0][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2137  Kfusion[1] = SK_MX[0]*(P[1][19] + P[1][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[1][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[1][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[1][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[1][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[1][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[1][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2138  Kfusion[2] = SK_MX[0]*(P[2][19] + P[2][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[2][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[2][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[2][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[2][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[2][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[2][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2139  Kfusion[3] = SK_MX[0]*(P[3][19] + P[3][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[3][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[3][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[3][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[3][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[3][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2140  Kfusion[4] = SK_MX[0]*(P[4][19] + P[4][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[4][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[4][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[4][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[4][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[4][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[4][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2141  Kfusion[5] = SK_MX[0]*(P[5][19] + P[5][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[5][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[5][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[5][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[5][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[5][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[5][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2142  Kfusion[6] = SK_MX[0]*(P[6][19] + P[6][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[6][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[6][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[6][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[6][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[6][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[6][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2143  Kfusion[7] = SK_MX[0]*(P[7][19] + P[7][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[7][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[7][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[7][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[7][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[7][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[7][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2144  Kfusion[8] = SK_MX[0]*(P[8][19] + P[8][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[8][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[8][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[8][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[8][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[8][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[8][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2145  Kfusion[9] = SK_MX[0]*(P[9][19] + P[9][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[9][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[9][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[9][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[9][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[9][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[9][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2146  Kfusion[10] = SK_MX[0]*(P[10][19] + P[10][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[10][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[10][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[10][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[10][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[10][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[10][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2147  Kfusion[11] = SK_MX[0]*(P[11][19] + P[11][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[11][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[11][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[11][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[11][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[11][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[11][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2148  Kfusion[12] = SK_MX[0]*(P[12][19] + P[12][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[12][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[12][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[12][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[12][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[12][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[12][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2149  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
2150  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_MX[0]*(P[13][19] + P[13][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[13][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[13][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[13][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[13][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[13][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[13][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2151  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit wind state estimation
2152  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
2153  Kfusion[14] = SK_MX[0]*(P[14][19] + P[14][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[14][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[14][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[14][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[14][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[14][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[14][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2154  Kfusion[15] = SK_MX[0]*(P[15][19] + P[15][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[15][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[15][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[15][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[15][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[15][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[15][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2155  } else {
2156  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2157  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2158  }
2159  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
2160  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2161  Kfusion[16] = SK_MX[0]*(P[16][19] + P[16][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[16][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[16][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[16][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[16][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[16][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[16][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2162  Kfusion[17] = SK_MX[0]*(P[17][19] + P[17][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[17][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[17][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[17][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[17][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[17][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[17][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2163  Kfusion[18] = SK_MX[0]*(P[18][19] + P[18][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[18][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[18][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[18][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[18][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[18][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2164  Kfusion[19] = SK_MX[0]*(P[19][19] + P[19][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[19][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[19][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[19][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[19][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[19][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[19][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2165  Kfusion[20] = SK_MX[0]*(P[20][19] + P[20][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[20][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[20][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[20][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[20][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[20][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[20][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2166  Kfusion[21] = SK_MX[0]*(P[21][19] + P[21][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[21][3]*SH_MAG[2] + P[21][0]*SK_MX[3] - P[21][2]*SK_MX[2] - P[21][16]*SK_MX[1] + P[21][17]*SK_MX[5] - P[21][18]*SK_MX[4]);
2167  } else {
2168  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
2169  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2170  }
2171  }
2172 
2173  // calculate the observation innovation variance
2174  varInnovMag[0] = 1.0f/SK_MX[0];
2175 
2176  // reset the observation index to 0 (we start by fusing the X measurement)
2177  obsIndex = 0;
2178 
2179  // set flags to indicate to other processes that fusion has been performed and is required on the next frame
2180  // this can be used by other fusion processes to avoid fusing on the same frame as this expensive step
2181  magFusePerformed = true;
2182  magFuseRequired = true;
2183  }
2184  else if (obsIndex == 1) // we are now fusing the Y measurement
2185  {
2186  // calculate observation jacobians
2187  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_MAG[i] = 0;
2188  H_MAG[0] = SH_MAG[2];
2189  H_MAG[1] = SH_MAG[1];
2190  H_MAG[2] = SH_MAG[0];
2191  H_MAG[3] = 2*magD*q2 - SH_MAG[8] - SH_MAG[7];
2192  H_MAG[16] = 2*q1*q2 - 2*q0*q3;
2193  H_MAG[17] = SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6];
2194  H_MAG[18] = 2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3;
2195  H_MAG[20] = 1;
2196 
2197  // calculate Kalman gain
