2302  Kfusion[12] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[12][21] + P[12][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[12][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[12][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[12][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[12][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[12][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[12][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2303  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
2304  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_MZ[0]*(P[13][21] + P[13][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[13][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[13][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[13][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[13][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[13][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[13][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2305  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit wind state estimation
2306  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
2307  Kfusion[14] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[14][21] + P[14][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[14][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[14][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[14][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[14][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[14][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[14][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2308  Kfusion[15] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[15][21] + P[15][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[15][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[15][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[15][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[15][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[15][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[15][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2309  } else {
2310  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2311  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2312  }
2313  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
2314  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2315  Kfusion[16] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[16][21] + P[16][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[16][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[16][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[16][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[16][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[16][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[16][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2316  Kfusion[17] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[17][21] + P[17][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[17][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[17][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[17][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[17][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[17][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[17][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2317  Kfusion[18] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[18][21] + P[18][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[18][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[18][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[18][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[18][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[18][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[18][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2318  Kfusion[19] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[19][21] + P[19][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[19][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[19][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[19][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[19][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[19][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[19][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2319  Kfusion[20] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[20][21] + P[20][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[20][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[20][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[20][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[20][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[20][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[20][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2320  Kfusion[21] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[21][21] + P[21][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[21][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[21][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[21][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[21][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[21][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[21][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2321  } else {
2322  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
2323  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2324  }
2325  }
2326 
2327  // calculate the observation innovation variance
2328  varInnovMag[2] = 1.0f/SK_MZ[0];
2329 
2330  // set flags to indicate to other processes that fusion has been performede and is required on the next frame
2331  // this can be used by other fusion processes to avoid fusing on the same frame as this expensive step
2332  magFusePerformed = true;
2333  magFuseRequired = false;
2334  }
2335  // calculate the measurement innovation
2336  innovMag[obsIndex] = MagPred[obsIndex] - magData[obsIndex];
2337  // calculate the innovation test ratio
2338  magTestRatio[obsIndex] = sq(innovMag[obsIndex]) / (sq(frontend._magInnovGate) * varInnovMag[obsIndex]);
2339  // check the last values from all components and set magnetometer health accordingly
2340  magHealth = (magTestRatio[0] < 1.0f && magTestRatio[1] < 1.0f && magTestRatio[2] < 1.0f);
2341  // Don't fuse unless all componenets pass. The exception is if the bad health has timed out and we are not a fly forward vehicle
2342  // In this case we might as well try using the magnetometer, but with a reduced weighting
2343  if (magHealth || ((magTestRatio[obsIndex] < 1.0f) && !assume_zero_sideslip() && magTimeout)) {
2344  // Attitude, velocity and position corrections are averaged across multiple prediction cycles between now and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
2345  // Don't do averaging of quaternion state corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
2346  bool highRates = ((magUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
2347  // Calculate the number of averaging frames left to go. This is required becasue magnetometer fusion is applied across three consecutive prediction cycles
2348  // There is no point averaging if the number of cycles left is less than 2
2349  float minorFramesToGo = float(magUpdateCountMax) - float(magUpdateCount);
2350  // correct the state vector or store corrections to be applied incrementally
2351  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++) {
2352  // If we are forced to use a bad compass in flight, we reduce the weighting by a factor of 4
2353  if (!magHealth && !constPosMode) {
2354  Kfusion[j] *= 0.25f;
2355  }
2356  // If in the air and there is no other form of heading reference or we are yawing rapidly which creates larger inertial yaw errors,
2357  // we strengthen the magnetometer attitude correction
2358  if (vehicleArmed && (constPosMode || highYawRate) && j <= 3) {
2359  Kfusion[j] *= 4.0f;
2360  }
2361  // We don't need to spread corrections for non-dynamic states or if we are in a constant postion mode
2362  // We can't spread corrections if there is not enough time remaining
2363  // We don't spread corrections to attitude states if we are rotating rapidly
2364  if ((j <= 3 && highRates) || j >= 10 || constPosMode || minorFramesToGo < 1.5f ) {
2365  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovMag[obsIndex];
2366  } else {
2367  // scale the correction based on the number of averaging frames left to go
2368  magIncrStateDelta[j] -= Kfusion[j] * innovMag[obsIndex] * (magUpdateCountMaxInv * float(magUpdateCountMax) / minorFramesToGo);
2369  }
2370  }
2371  // normalise the quaternion states
2372  state.quat.normalize();
2373  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
2374  // take advantage of the empty columns in KH to reduce the
2375  // number of operations
2376  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2377  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=3; j++) {
2378  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_MAG[j];
2379  }
2380  for (uint8_t j = 4; j<=15; j++) {
2381  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2382  }
2383  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2384  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) {
2385  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_MAG[j];
2386  }
2387  } else {
2388  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) {
2389  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2390  }
2391  }
2392  }
2393  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2394  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++) {
2395  KHP[i][j] = 0;
2396  for (uint8_t k = 0; k<=3; k++) {
2397  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
2398  }
2399  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2400  for (uint8_t k = 16; k<=21; k++) {
2401  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
2402  }
2403  }
2404  }
2405  }
2406  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2407  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++) {
2408  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
2409  }
2410  }
2411  }
2412 
2413  // force the covariance matrix to be symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent
2414  // ill-condiioning.
2415  ForceSymmetry();
2416  ConstrainVariances();
2417 }
2418 
2419 /*
2420 Estimation of terrain offset using a single state EKF
2421 The filter can fuse motion compensated optiocal flow rates and range finder measurements
2422 */
2423 void NavEKF_core::EstimateTerrainOffset()
2424 {
2425  // start performance timer
2426  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_OpticalFlowEKF);
2427 
2428  // constrain height above ground to be above range measured on ground
2429  float heightAboveGndEst = max((terrainState - state.position.z), rngOnGnd);
2430 
2431  // calculate a predicted LOS rate squared
2432  float velHorizSq = sq(state.velocity.x) + sq(state.velocity.y);
2433  float losRateSq = velHorizSq / sq(heightAboveGndEst);
2434 
2435  // don't update terrain offset state if there is no range finder and not generating enough LOS rate, or without GPS, as it is poorly observable
2436  if (!fuseRngData && (gpsNotAvailable || PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE || velHorizSq < 25.0f || losRateSq < 0.01f || onGround)) {
2437  inhibitGndState = true;
2438  } else {
2439  inhibitGndState = false;
2440  // record the time we last updated the terrain offset state
2441  gndHgtValidTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2442 
2443  // propagate ground position state noise each time this is called using the difference in position since the last observations and an RMS gradient assumption
2444  // limit distance to prevent intialisation afer bad gps causing bad numerical conditioning
2445  float distanceTravelledSq = sq(statesAtRngTime.position[0] - prevPosN) + sq(statesAtRngTime.position[1] - prevPosE);
2446  distanceTravelledSq = min(distanceTravelledSq, 100.0f);
2447  prevPosN = statesAtRngTime.position[0];
2448  prevPosE = statesAtRngTime.position[1];
2449 
2450  // in addition to a terrain gradient error model, we also have a time based error growth that is scaled using the gradient parameter
2451  float timeLapsed = min(0.001f * (imuSampleTime_ms - timeAtLastAuxEKF_ms), 1.0f);
2452  float Pincrement = (distanceTravelledSq * sq(0.01f*float(frontend._gndGradientSigma))) + sq(float(frontend._gndGradientSigma) * timeLapsed);
2453  Popt += Pincrement;
2454  timeAtLastAuxEKF_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2455 
2456  // fuse range finder data
2457  if (fuseRngData) {
2458  // predict range
2459  float predRngMeas = max((terrainState - statesAtRngTime.position[2]),rngOnGnd) / Tnb_flow.c.z;
2460 
2461  // Copy required states to local variable names
2462  float q0 = statesAtRngTime.quat[0]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2463  float q1 = statesAtRngTime.quat[1]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2464  float q2 = statesAtRngTime.quat[2]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2465  float q3 = statesAtRngTime.quat[3]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2466 
2467  // Set range finder measurement noise variance. TODO make this a function of range and tilt to allow for sensor, alignment and AHRS errors
2468  float R_RNG = 0.5f;
2469 
2470  // calculate Kalman gain
2471  float SK_RNG = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
2472  float K_RNG = Popt/(SK_RNG*(R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG)));
2473 
2474  // Calculate the innovation variance for data logging
2475  varInnovRng = (R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG));
2476 
2477  // constrain terrain height to be below the vehicle
2478  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtRngTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2479 
2480  // Calculate the measurement innovation
2481  innovRng = predRngMeas - rngMea;
2482 
2483  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2484  auxRngTestRatio = sq(innovRng) / (sq(frontend._rngInnovGate) * varInnovRng);
2485 
2486  // Check the innovation for consistency and don't fuse if > 5Sigma
2487  if ((sq(innovRng)*SK_RNG) < 25.0f)
2488  {
2489  // correct the state
2490  terrainState -= K_RNG * innovRng;
2491 
2492  // constrain the state
2493  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtRngTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2494 
2495  // correct the covariance
2496  Popt = Popt - sq(Popt)/(SK_RNG*(R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG))*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3)));
2497 
2498  // prevent the state variance from becoming negative
2499  Popt = max(Popt,0.0f);
2500 
2501  }
2502  }
2503 
2504  if (fuseOptFlowData) {
2505 
2506  Vector3f relVelSensor; // velocity of sensor relative to ground in sensor axes
2507  float losPred; // predicted optical flow angular rate measurement
2508  float q0 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[0]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2509  float q1 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[1]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2510  float q2 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[2]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2511  float q3 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[3]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2512  float K_OPT;
2513  float H_OPT;
2514 
2515  // predict range to centre of image
2516  float flowRngPred = max((terrainState - statesAtFlowTime.position[2]),rngOnGnd) / Tnb_flow.c.z;
2517 
2518  // constrain terrain height to be below the vehicle
2519  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtFlowTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2520 
2521  // calculate relative velocity in sensor frame
2522  relVelSensor = Tnb_flow*statesAtFlowTime.velocity;
2523 
2524  // divide velocity by range, subtract body rates and apply scale factor to
2525  // get predicted sensed angular optical rates relative to X and Y sensor axes
2526  losPred = relVelSensor.length()/flowRngPred;
2527 
2528  // calculate innovations
2529  auxFlowObsInnov = losPred - sqrtf(sq(flowRadXYcomp[0]) + sq(flowRadXYcomp[1]));
2530 
2531  // calculate observation jacobian
2532  float t3 = sq(q0);
2533  float t4 = sq(q1);
2534  float t5 = sq(q2);
2535  float t6 = sq(q3);
2536  float t10 = q0*q3*2.0f;
2537  float t11 = q1*q2*2.0f;
2538  float t14 = t3+t4-t5-t6;
2539  float t15 = t14*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.x;
2540  float t16 = t10+t11;
2541  float t17 = t16*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.y;
2542  float t18 = q0*q2*2.0f;
2543  float t19 = q1*q3*2.0f;
2544  float t20 = t18-t19;
2545  float t21 = t20*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.z;
2546  float t2 = t15+t17-t21;
2547  float t7 = t3-t4-t5+t6;
2548  float t8 = statesAtFlowTime.position[2]-terrainState;
2549  float t9 = 1.0f/sq(t8);
2550  float t24 = t3-t4+t5-t6;
2551  float t25 = t24*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.y;
2552  float t26 = t10-t11;
2553  float t27 = t26*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.x;
2554  float t28 = q0*q1*2.0f;
2555  float t29 = q2*q3*2.0f;
2556  float t30 = t28+t29;
2557  float t31 = t30*statesAtFlowTime.velocity.z;
2558  float t12 = t25-t27+t31;
2559  float t13 = sq(t7);
2560  float t22 = sq(t2);
2561  float t23 = 1.0f/(t8*t8*t8);
2562  float t32 = sq(t12);
2563  H_OPT = 0.5f*(t13*t22*t23*2.0f+t13*t23*t32*2.0f)/sqrtf(t9*t13*t22+t9*t13*t32);
2564 
2565  // calculate innovation variances
2566  auxFlowObsInnovVar = H_OPT*Popt*H_OPT + R_LOS;
2567 
2568  // calculate Kalman gain
2569  K_OPT = Popt*H_OPT/auxFlowObsInnovVar;
2570 
2571  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2572  auxFlowTestRatio = sq(auxFlowObsInnov) / (sq(frontend._flowInnovGate) * auxFlowObsInnovVar);
2573 
2574  // don't fuse if optical flow data is outside valid range
2575  if (max(flowRadXY[0],flowRadXY[1]) < frontend._maxFlowRate) {
2576 
2577  // correct the state
2578  terrainState -= K_OPT * auxFlowObsInnov;
2579 
2580  // constrain the state
2581  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtFlowTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2582 
2583  // correct the covariance
2584  Popt = Popt - K_OPT * H_OPT * Popt;
2585 
2586  // prevent the state variances from becoming negative
2587  Popt = max(Popt,0.0f);
2588  }
2589  }
2590  }
2591 
2592  // stop the performance timer
2593  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_OpticalFlowEKF);
2594 }
2595 
2596 void NavEKF_core::FuseOptFlow()
2597 {
2598  Vector22 H_LOS;
2599  Vector8 tempVar;
2600  Vector3f relVelSensor;
2601 
2602  uint8_t obsIndex = flow_state.obsIndex;
2603  ftype &q0 = flow_state.q0;
2604  ftype &q1 = flow_state.q1;
2605  ftype &q2 = flow_state.q2;
2606  ftype &q3 = flow_state.q3;
2607  ftype *SH_LOS = &flow_state.SH_LOS[0];
2608  ftype *SK_LOS = &flow_state.SK_LOS[0];
2609  ftype &vn = flow_state.vn;
2610  ftype &ve = flow_state.ve;
2611  ftype &vd = flow_state.vd;
2612  ftype &pd = flow_state.pd;
2613  ftype *losPred = &flow_state.losPred[0];
2614 
2615  // Copy required states to local variable names
2616  q0 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[0];
2617  q1 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[1];
2618  q2 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[2];
2619  q3 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[3];
2620  vn = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[0];
2621  ve = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[1];
2622  vd = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[2];
2623  pd = statesAtFlowTime.position[2];
2624 
2625  // constrain height above ground to be above range measured on ground
2626  float heightAboveGndEst = max((terrainState - pd), rngOnGnd);
2627  // Calculate observation jacobians and Kalman gains
2628  if (obsIndex == 0) {
2629  // calculate range from ground plain to centre of sensor fov assuming flat earth
2630  float range = constrain_float((heightAboveGndEst/Tnb_flow.c.z),rngOnGnd,1000.0f);
2631 
2632  // calculate relative velocity in sensor frame
2633  relVelSensor = Tnb_flow*statesAtFlowTime.velocity;
2634 
2635  // divide velocity by range to get predicted angular LOS rates relative to X and Y axes
2636  losPred[0] = relVelSensor.y/range;
2637  losPred[1] = -relVelSensor.x/range;
2638 
2639 
2640  // Calculate common expressions for observation jacobians
2641  SH_LOS[0] = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
2642  SH_LOS[1] = vn*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3)) - vd*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) + ve*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
2643  SH_LOS[2] = ve*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3)) + vd*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) - vn*(2*q0*q3 - 2*q1*q2);
2644  SH_LOS[3] = -1.0f/heightAboveGndEst;
2645 
2646  // Calculate common expressions for Kalman gains
2647  // calculate innovation variance for Y axis observation
2648  varInnovOptFlow[1] = (R_LOS + (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3])*(P[0][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) + (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2690 
2691  // calculate Kalman gains for X LOS rate
2692  Kfusion[0] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[0][0]*tempVar[0] + P[0][1]*tempVar[1] - P[0][3]*tempVar[2] + P[0][2]*tempVar[7] - P[0][4]*tempVar[3] + P[0][6]*tempVar[4] - P[0][9]*tempVar[5] + P[0][5]*tempVar[6]);
2693  Kfusion[1] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[1][0]*tempVar[0] + P[1][1]*tempVar[1] - P[1][3]*tempVar[2] + P[1][2]*tempVar[7] - P[1][4]*tempVar[3] + P[1][6]*tempVar[4] - P[1][9]*tempVar[5] + P[1][5]*tempVar[6]);
2694  Kfusion[2] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[2][0]*tempVar[0] + P[2][1]*tempVar[1] - P[2][3]*tempVar[2] + P[2][2]*tempVar[7] - P[2][4]*tempVar[3] + P[2][6]*tempVar[4] - P[2][9]*tempVar[5] + P[2][5]*tempVar[6]);
2695  Kfusion[3] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[3][0]*tempVar[0] + P[3][1]*tempVar[1] - P[3][3]*tempVar[2] + P[3][2]*tempVar[7] - P[3][4]*tempVar[3] + P[3][6]*tempVar[4] - P[3][9]*tempVar[5] + P[3][5]*tempVar[6]);
2696  Kfusion[4] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[4][0]*tempVar[0] + P[4][1]*tempVar[1] - P[4][3]*tempVar[2] + P[4][2]*tempVar[7] - P[4][4]*tempVar[3] + P[4][6]*tempVar[4] - P[4][9]*tempVar[5] + P[4][5]*tempVar[6]);
2697  Kfusion[5] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[5][0]*tempVar[0] + P[5][1]*tempVar[1] - P[5][3]*tempVar[2] + P[5][2]*tempVar[7] - P[5][4]*tempVar[3] + P[5][6]*tempVar[4] - P[5][9]*tempVar[5] + P[5][5]*tempVar[6]);
2698  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical velocity as it can produce height offsets
2699  Kfusion[6] = 0.0f;//-SK_LOS[1]*(P[6][0]*tempVar[0] + P[6][1]*tempVar[1] - P[6][3]*tempVar[2] + P[6][2]*tempVar[7] - P[6][4]*tempVar[3] + P[6][6]*tempVar[4] - P[6][9]*tempVar[5] + P[6][5]*tempVar[6]);
2700  Kfusion[7] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[7][0]*tempVar[0] + P[7][1]*tempVar[1] - P[7][3]*tempVar[2] + P[7][2]*tempVar[7] - P[7][4]*tempVar[3] + P[7][6]*tempVar[4] - P[7][9]*tempVar[5] + P[7][5]*tempVar[6]);
2701  Kfusion[8] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[8][0]*tempVar[0] + P[8][1]*tempVar[1] - P[8][3]*tempVar[2] + P[8][2]*tempVar[7] - P[8][4]*tempVar[3] + P[8][6]*tempVar[4] - P[8][9]*tempVar[5] + P[8][5]*tempVar[6]);
2702  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical position as it can produce height offsets
2703  Kfusion[9] = 0.0f;//-SK_LOS[1]*(P[9][0]*tempVar[0] + P[9][1]*tempVar[1] - P[9][3]*tempVar[2] + P[9][2]*tempVar[7] - P[9][4]*tempVar[3] + P[9][6]*tempVar[4] - P[9][9]*tempVar[5] + P[9][5]*tempVar[6]);
2704  Kfusion[10] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[10][0]*tempVar[0] + P[10][1]*tempVar[1] - P[10][3]*tempVar[2] + P[10][2]*tempVar[7] - P[10][4]*tempVar[3] + P[10][6]*tempVar[4] - P[10][9]*tempVar[5] + P[10][5]*tempVar[6]);
2705  Kfusion[11] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[11][0]*tempVar[0] + P[11][1]*tempVar[1] - P[11][3]*tempVar[2] + P[11][2]*tempVar[7] - P[11][4]*tempVar[3] + P[11][6]*tempVar[4] - P[11][9]*tempVar[5] + P[11][5]*tempVar[6]);
2706  Kfusion[12] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[12][0]*tempVar[0] + P[12][1]*tempVar[1] - P[12][3]*tempVar[2] + P[12][2]*tempVar[7] - P[12][4]*tempVar[3] + P[12][6]*tempVar[4] - P[12][9]*tempVar[5] + P[12][5]*tempVar[6]);
2707  // only height measurements are allowed to modify the Z bias state to improve the stability of the estimate
2708  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//Kfusion[13] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[13][0]*tempVar[0] + P[13][1]*tempVar[1] - P[13][3]*tempVar[2] + P[13][2]*tempVar[7] - P[13][4]*tempVar[3] + P[13][6]*tempVar[4] - P[13][9]*tempVar[5] + P[13][5]*tempVar[6]);
2709  if (inhibitWindStates) {
2710  Kfusion[14] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[14][0]*tempVar[0] + P[14][1]*tempVar[1] - P[14][3]*tempVar[2] + P[14][2]*tempVar[7] - P[14][4]*tempVar[3] + P[14][6]*tempVar[4] - P[14][9]*tempVar[5] + P[14][5]*tempVar[6]);
2711  Kfusion[15] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[15][0]*tempVar[0] + P[15][1]*tempVar[1] - P[15][3]*tempVar[2] + P[15][2]*tempVar[7] - P[15][4]*tempVar[3] + P[15][6]*tempVar[4] - P[15][9]*tempVar[5] + P[15][5]*tempVar[6]);
2712  } else {
2713  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2714  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2715  }
2716  if (inhibitMagStates) {
2717  Kfusion[16] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[16][0]*tempVar[0] + P[16][1]*tempVar[1] - P[16][3]*tempVar[2] + P[16][2]*tempVar[7] - P[16][4]*tempVar[3] + P[16][6]*tempVar[4] - P[16][9]*tempVar[5] + P[16][5]*tempVar[6]);
2718  Kfusion[17] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[17][0]*tempVar[0] + P[17][1]*tempVar[1] - P[17][3]*tempVar[2] + P[17][2]*tempVar[7] - P[17][4]*tempVar[3] + P[17][6]*tempVar[4] - P[17][9]*tempVar[5] + P[17][5]*tempVar[6]);
2719  Kfusion[18] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[18][0]*tempVar[0] + P[18][1]*tempVar[1] - P[18][3]*tempVar[2] + P[18][2]*tempVar[7] - P[18][4]*tempVar[3] + P[18][6]*tempVar[4] - P[18][9]*tempVar[5] + P[18][5]*tempVar[6]);
2720  Kfusion[19] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[19][0]*tempVar[0] + P[19][1]*tempVar[1] - P[19][3]*tempVar[2] + P[19][2]*tempVar[7] - P[19][4]*tempVar[3] + P[19][6]*tempVar[4] - P[19][9]*tempVar[5] + P[19][5]*tempVar[6]);
2721  Kfusion[20] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[20][0]*tempVar[0] + P[20][1]*tempVar[1] - P[20][3]*tempVar[2] + P[20][2]*tempVar[7] - P[20][4]*tempVar[3] + P[20][6]*tempVar[4] - P[20][9]*tempVar[5] + P[20][5]*tempVar[6]);
2722  Kfusion[21] = -SK_LOS[1]*(P[21][0]*tempVar[0] + P[21][1]*tempVar[1] - P[21][3]*tempVar[2] + P[21][2]*tempVar[7] - P[21][4]*tempVar[3] + P[21][6]*tempVar[4] - P[21][9]*tempVar[5] + P[21][5]*tempVar[6]);
2723  } else {
2724  for (uint8_t i = 16; i <= 21; i++) {
2725  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2726  }
2727  }
2728  // calculate innovation for X axis observation
2729  innovOptFlow[0] = losPred[0] - flowRadXYcomp[0];
2730 
2731  } else if (obsIndex == 1) {
2732 
2733  // calculate intermediate common variables
2734  tempVar[0] = SK_LOS[2] + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SK_LOS[9];
2735  tempVar[1] = SK_LOS[5] - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SK_LOS[9];
2736  tempVar[2] = SK_LOS[3] + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SK_LOS[9];
2737  tempVar[3] = SK_LOS[4] + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SK_LOS[9];
2738  tempVar[4] = SH_LOS[0]*SK_LOS[9]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
2739  tempVar[5] = SH_LOS[0]*SK_LOS[9]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3);
2740  tempVar[6] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1]*SK_LOS[7];
2741  tempVar[7] = SH_LOS[0]*SK_LOS[8]*SK_LOS[9];
2742 
2743  // Calculate observation jacobians for Y LOS rate
2744  memset(&H_LOS[0], 0, sizeof(H_LOS));
2745  H_LOS[0] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3];
2746  H_LOS[1] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3];
2747  H_LOS[2] = - SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) - 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3];
2748  H_LOS[3] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3];
2749  H_LOS[4] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3));
2750  H_LOS[5] = SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
2751  H_LOS[6] = -SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3);
2752  H_LOS[9] = -(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(heightAboveGndEst);
2753 
2754  // Calculate Kalman gains for Y LOS rate
2755  Kfusion[0] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[0][0]*tempVar[0] + P[0][1]*tempVar[1] - P[0][2]*tempVar[2] + P[0][3]*tempVar[3] + P[0][5]*tempVar[4] - P[0][6]*tempVar[5] - P[0][9]*tempVar[6] + P[0][4]*tempVar[7]);
2756  Kfusion[1] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[1][0]*tempVar[0] + P[1][1]*tempVar[1] - P[1][2]*tempVar[2] + P[1][3]*tempVar[3] + P[1][5]*tempVar[4] - P[1][6]*tempVar[5] - P[1][9]*tempVar[6] + P[1][4]*tempVar[7]);
2757  Kfusion[2] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[2][0]*tempVar[0] + P[2][1]*tempVar[1] - P[2][2]*tempVar[2] + P[2][3]*tempVar[3] + P[2][5]*tempVar[4] - P[2][6]*tempVar[5] - P[2][9]*tempVar[6] + P[2][4]*tempVar[7]);
2758  Kfusion[3] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[3][0]*tempVar[0] + P[3][1]*tempVar[1] - P[3][2]*tempVar[2] + P[3][3]*tempVar[3] + P[3][5]*tempVar[4] - P[3][6]*tempVar[5] - P[3][9]*tempVar[6] + P[3][4]*tempVar[7]);
2759  Kfusion[4] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[4][0]*tempVar[0] + P[4][1]*tempVar[1] - P[4][2]*tempVar[2] + P[4][3]*tempVar[3] + P[4][5]*tempVar[4] - P[4][6]*tempVar[5] - P[4][9]*tempVar[6] + P[4][4]*tempVar[7]);
2760  Kfusion[5] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[5][0]*tempVar[0] + P[5][1]*tempVar[1] - P[5][2]*tempVar[2] + P[5][3]*tempVar[3] + P[5][5]*tempVar[4] - P[5][6]*tempVar[5] - P[5][9]*tempVar[6] + P[5][4]*tempVar[7]);
2761  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical velocity as it can produce height offsets
2762  Kfusion[6] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[6][0]*tempVar[0] + P[6][1]*tempVar[1] - P[6][2]*tempVar[2] + P[6][3]*tempVar[3] + P[6][5]*tempVar[4] - P[6][6]*tempVar[5] - P[6][9]*tempVar[6] + P[6][4]*tempVar[7]);
2763  Kfusion[7] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[7][0]*tempVar[0] + P[7][1]*tempVar[1] - P[7][2]*tempVar[2] + P[7][3]*tempVar[3] + P[7][5]*tempVar[4] - P[7][6]*tempVar[5] - P[7][9]*tempVar[6] + P[7][4]*tempVar[7]);
2764  Kfusion[8] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[8][0]*tempVar[0] + P[8][1]*tempVar[1] - P[8][2]*tempVar[2] + P[8][3]*tempVar[3] + P[8][5]*tempVar[4] - P[8][6]*tempVar[5] - P[8][9]*tempVar[6] + P[8][4]*tempVar[7]);
2765  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical position as it can produce height offsets
2766  Kfusion[9] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[9][0]*tempVar[0] + P[9][1]*tempVar[1] - P[9][2]*tempVar[2] + P[9][3]*tempVar[3] + P[9][5]*tempVar[4] - P[9][6]*tempVar[5] - P[9][9]*tempVar[6] + P[9][4]*tempVar[7]);
2767  Kfusion[10] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[10][0]*tempVar[0] + P[10][1]*tempVar[1] - P[10][2]*tempVar[2] + P[10][3]*tempVar[3] + P[10][5]*tempVar[4] - P[10][6]*tempVar[5] - P[10][9]*tempVar[6] + P[10][4]*tempVar[7]);
2768  Kfusion[11] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[11][0]*tempVar[0] + P[11][1]*tempVar[1] - P[11][2]*tempVar[2] + P[11][3]*tempVar[3] + P[11][5]*tempVar[4] - P[11][6]*tempVar[5] - P[11][9]*tempVar[6] + P[11][4]*tempVar[7]);
2769  Kfusion[12] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[12][0]*tempVar[0] + P[12][1]*tempVar[1] - P[12][2]*tempVar[2] + P[12][3]*tempVar[3] + P[12][5]*tempVar[4] - P[12][6]*tempVar[5] - P[12][9]*tempVar[6] + P[12][4]*tempVar[7]);
2770  // only height measurements are allowed to modify the Z bias state to improve the stability of the estimate
2771  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[13][0]*tempVar[0] + P[13][1]*tempVar[1] - P[13][2]*tempVar[2] + P[13][3]*tempVar[3] + P[13][5]*tempVar[4] - P[13][6]*tempVar[5] - P[13][9]*tempVar[6] + P[13][4]*tempVar[7]);
2772  if (inhibitWindStates) {
2773  Kfusion[14] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[14][0]*tempVar[0] + P[14][1]*tempVar[1] - P[14][2]*tempVar[2] + P[14][3]*tempVar[3] + P[14][5]*tempVar[4] - P[14][6]*tempVar[5] - P[14][9]*tempVar[6] + P[14][4]*tempVar[7]);
2774  Kfusion[15] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[15][0]*tempVar[0] + P[15][1]*tempVar[1] - P[15][2]*tempVar[2] + P[15][3]*tempVar[3] + P[15][5]*tempVar[4] - P[15][6]*tempVar[5] - P[15][9]*tempVar[6] + P[15][4]*tempVar[7]);
2775  } else {
2776  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2777  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2778  }
2779  if (inhibitMagStates) {
2780  Kfusion[16] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[16][0]*tempVar[0] + P[16][1]*tempVar[1] - P[16][2]*tempVar[2] + P[16][3]*tempVar[3] + P[16][5]*tempVar[4] - P[16][6]*tempVar[5] - P[16][9]*tempVar[6] + P[16][4]*tempVar[7]);
2781  Kfusion[17] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[17][0]*tempVar[0] + P[17][1]*tempVar[1] - P[17][2]*tempVar[2] + P[17][3]*tempVar[3] + P[17][5]*tempVar[4] - P[17][6]*tempVar[5] - P[17][9]*tempVar[6] + P[17][4]*tempVar[7]);
2782  Kfusion[18] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[18][0]*tempVar[0] + P[18][1]*tempVar[1] - P[18][2]*tempVar[2] + P[18][3]*tempVar[3] + P[18][5]*tempVar[4] - P[18][6]*tempVar[5] - P[18][9]*tempVar[6] + P[18][4]*tempVar[7]);
2783  Kfusion[19] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[19][0]*tempVar[0] + P[19][1]*tempVar[1] - P[19][2]*tempVar[2] + P[19][3]*tempVar[3] + P[19][5]*tempVar[4] - P[19][6]*tempVar[5] - P[19][9]*tempVar[6] + P[19][4]*tempVar[7]);
2784  Kfusion[20] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[20][0]*tempVar[0] + P[20][1]*tempVar[1] - P[20][2]*tempVar[2] + P[20][3]*tempVar[3] + P[20][5]*tempVar[4] - P[20][6]*tempVar[5] - P[20][9]*tempVar[6] + P[20][4]*tempVar[7]);
2785  Kfusion[21] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[21][0]*tempVar[0] + P[21][1]*tempVar[1] - P[21][2]*tempVar[2] + P[21][3]*tempVar[3] + P[21][5]*tempVar[4] - P[21][6]*tempVar[5] - P[21][9]*tempVar[6] + P[21][4]*tempVar[7]);
2786  } else {
2787  for (uint8_t i = 16; i <= 21; i++) {
2788  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2789  }
2790  }
2791  // calculate innovation for Y observation
2792  innovOptFlow[1] = losPred[1] - flowRadXYcomp[1];
2793 
2794  }
2795 
2796  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2797  flowTestRatio[obsIndex] = sq(innovOptFlow[obsIndex]) / (sq(frontend._flowInnovGate) * varInnovOptFlow[obsIndex]);
2798 
2799  // Check the innovation for consistency and don't fuse if out of bounds or flow is too fast to be reliable
2800  if ((flowTestRatio[obsIndex]) < 1.0f && (flowRadXY[obsIndex] < frontend._maxFlowRate)) {
2801  // record the last time both X and Y observations were accepted for fusion
2802  if (obsIndex == 0) {
2803  flowXfailed = false;
2804  } else if (!flowXfailed) {
2805  prevFlowFuseTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2806  }
2807  // Attitude, velocity and position corrections are averaged across multiple prediction cycles between now and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
2808  // Don't do averaging of quaternion state corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
2809  bool highRates = ((flowUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
2810  // Calculate the number of averaging frames left to go.
2811  // There is no point averaging if the number of cycles left is less than 2
2812  float minorFramesToGo = float(flowUpdateCountMax) - float(flowUpdateCount);
2813  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2814  if ((i <= 3 && highRates) || i >= 10 || minorFramesToGo < 1.5f) {
2815  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * innovOptFlow[obsIndex];
2816  } else {
2817  flowIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovOptFlow[obsIndex] * (flowUpdateCountMaxInv * float(flowUpdateCountMax) / minorFramesToGo);
2818  }
2819  }
2820  // normalise the quaternion states
2821  state.quat.normalize();
2822  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
2823  // take advantage of the empty columns in KH to reduce the
2824  // number of operations
2825  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
2826  {
2827  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 6; j++)
2828  {
2829  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_LOS[j];
2830  }
2831  for (uint8_t j = 7; j <= 8; j++)
2832  {
2833  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2834  }
2835  KH[i][9] = Kfusion[i] * H_LOS[9];
2836  for (uint8_t j = 10; j <= 21; j++)
2837  {
2838  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2839  }
2840  }
2841  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
2842  {
2843  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 21; j++)
2844  {
2845  KHP[i][j] = 0.0f;
2846  for (uint8_t k = 0; k <= 6; k++)
2847  {
2848  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
2849  }
2850  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][9] * P[9][j];
2851  }
2852  }
2853  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
2854  {
2855  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 21; j++)
2856  {
2857  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
2858  }
2859  }
2860  } else if (obsIndex == 0) {
2861  // store the fact we have failed the X conponent so that a combined X and Y axis pass/fail can be calculated next time round
2862  flowXfailed = true;
2863  }
2864 
2865  ForceSymmetry();
2866  ConstrainVariances();
2867 
2868 }
2869 
2870 // fuse true airspeed measurements
2871 void NavEKF_core::FuseAirspeed()
2872 {
2873  // start performance timer
2874  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_FuseAirspeed);
2875 
2876  // declarations
2877  float vn;
2878  float ve;
2879  float vd;
2880  float vwn;
2881  float vwe;
2882  float EAS2TAS = _ahrs->get_EAS2TAS();
2883  const float R_TAS = sq(constrain_float(frontend._easNoise, 0.5f, 5.0f) * constrain_float(EAS2TAS, 0.9f, 10.0f));
2884  Vector3f SH_TAS;
2885  float SK_TAS;
2886  Vector22 H_TAS;
2887  float VtasPred;
2888 
2889  // health is set bad until test passed
2890  tasHealth = false;
2891 
2892  // copy required states to local variable names
2893  vn = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.x;
2894  ve = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.y;
2895  vd = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.z;
2896  vwn = statesAtVtasMeasTime.wind_vel.x;
2897  vwe = statesAtVtasMeasTime.wind_vel.y;
2898 
2899  // calculate the predicted airspeed
2900  VtasPred = pythagorous3((ve - vwe) , (vn - vwn) , vd);
2901  // perform fusion of True Airspeed measurement
2902  if (VtasPred > 1.0f)
2903  {
2904  // calculate observation jacobians
2905  SH_TAS[0] = 1.0f/VtasPred;
2906  SH_TAS[1] = (SH_TAS[0]*(2*ve - 2*vwe))/2;
2907  SH_TAS[2] = (SH_TAS[0]*(2*vn - 2*vwn))/2;
2908  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_TAS[i] = 0.0f;
2909  H_TAS[4] = SH_TAS[2];
2910  H_TAS[5] = SH_TAS[1];
2911  H_TAS[6] = vd*SH_TAS[0];
2912  H_TAS[14] = -SH_TAS[2];
2913  H_TAS[15] = -SH_TAS[1];
2914 
2915  // calculate Kalman gains
2916  float temp = (R_TAS + SH_TAS[2]*(P[4][4]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][4]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][4]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][4]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) + SH_TAS[1]*(P[4][5]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][5]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][5]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][5]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) - SH_TAS[2]*(P[4][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][14]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][14]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][14]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][14]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) - SH_TAS[1]*(P[4][15]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][15]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][15]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][15]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) + vd*SH_TAS[0]*(P[4][6]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][6]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][6]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][6]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]));
2917  if (temp >= R_TAS) {
2918  SK_TAS = 1.0f / temp;
2919  faultStatus.bad_airspeed = false;
2920  } else {
2921  // the calculation is badly conditioned, so we cannot perform fusion on this step
2922  // we increase the wind state variances and try again next time
2923  P[14][14] += 0.05f*R_TAS;
2924  P[15][15] += 0.05f*R_TAS;
2925  faultStatus.bad_airspeed = true;
2926  return;
2927  }
2928  Kfusion[0] = SK_TAS*(P[0][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[0][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[0][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[0][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[0][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2929  Kfusion[1] = SK_TAS*(P[1][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[1][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[1][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[1][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[1][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2930  Kfusion[2] = SK_TAS*(P[2][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[2][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[2][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[2][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[2][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2931  Kfusion[3] = SK_TAS*(P[3][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[3][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[3][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[3][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[3][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2932  Kfusion[4] = SK_TAS*(P[4][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[4][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[4][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[4][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[4][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2933  Kfusion[5] = SK_TAS*(P[5][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[5][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[5][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[5][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2934  Kfusion[6] = SK_TAS*(P[6][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[6][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[6][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[6][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2935  Kfusion[7] = SK_TAS*(P[7][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[7][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[7][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[7][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[7][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2936  Kfusion[8] = SK_TAS*(P[8][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[8][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[8][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[8][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[8][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2937  Kfusion[9] = SK_TAS*(P[9][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[9][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[9][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[9][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[9][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2938  Kfusion[10] = SK_TAS*(P[10][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[10][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[10][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[10][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[10][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2939  Kfusion[11] = SK_TAS*(P[11][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[11][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[11][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[11][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[11][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2940  Kfusion[12] = SK_TAS*(P[12][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[12][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[12][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[12][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[12][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2941  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
2942  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_TAS*(P[13][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[13][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[13][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[13][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[13][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2943  Kfusion[14] = SK_TAS*(P[14][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[14][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[14][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[14][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2944  Kfusion[15] = SK_TAS*(P[15][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[15][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[15][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[15][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2945  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
2946  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2947  Kfusion[16] = SK_TAS*(P[16][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[16][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[16][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[16][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[16][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2948  Kfusion[17] = SK_TAS*(P[17][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[17][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[17][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[17][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[17][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2949  Kfusion[18] = SK_TAS*(P[18][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[18][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[18][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[18][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[18][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2950  Kfusion[19] = SK_TAS*(P[19][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[19][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[19][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[19][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[19][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2951  Kfusion[20] = SK_TAS*(P[20][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[20][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[20][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[20][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[20][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2952  Kfusion[21] = SK_TAS*(P[21][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[21][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[21][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[21][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[21][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
2953  } else {
2954  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
2955  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2956  }
2957  }
2958 
2959  // calculate measurement innovation variance
2960  varInnovVtas = 1.0f/SK_TAS;
2961 
2962  // calculate measurement innovation
2963  innovVtas = VtasPred - VtasMeas;
2964 
2965  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2966  tasTestRatio = sq(innovVtas) / (sq(frontend._tasInnovGate) * varInnovVtas);
2967 
2968  // fail if the ratio is > 1, but don't fail if bad IMU data
2969  tasHealth = ((tasTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
2970  tasTimeout = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastTasPassTime) > tasRetryTime;
2971 
2972  // test the ratio before fusing data, forcing fusion if airspeed and position are timed out as we have no choice but to try and use airspeed to constrain error growth
2973  if (tasHealth || (tasTimeout && posTimeout))
2974  {
2975 
2976  // restart the counter
2977  lastTasPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
2978 
2979  // correct the state vector
2980  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
2981  {
2982  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovVtas;
2983  }
2984 
2985  state.quat.normalize();
2986 
2987  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
2988  // take advantage of the empty columns in H to reduce the number of operations
2989  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
2990  {
2991  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=3; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2992  for (uint8_t j = 4; j<=6; j++)
2993  {
2994  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_TAS[j];
2995  }
2996  for (uint8_t j = 7; j<=13; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2997  for (uint8_t j = 14; j<=15; j++)
2998  {
2999  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_TAS[j];
3000  }
3001  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3002  }
3003  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3004  {
3005  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3006  {
3007  KHP[i][j] = 0;
3008  for (uint8_t k = 4; k<=6; k++)
3009  {
3010  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3011  }
3012  for (uint8_t k = 14; k<=15; k++)
3013  {
3014  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3015  }
3016  }
3017  }
3018  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3019  {
3020  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3021  {
3022  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
3023  }
3024  }
3025  }
3026  }
3027 
3028  // force the covariance matrix to me symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
3029  ForceSymmetry();
3030  ConstrainVariances();
3031 
3032  // stop performance timer
3033  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_FuseAirspeed);
3034 }
3035 
3036 // fuse sythetic sideslip measurement of zero
3037 void NavEKF_core::FuseSideslip()
3038 {
3039  // start performance timer
3040  hal.util->perf_begin(_perf_FuseSideslip);
3041 
3042  // declarations
3043  float q0;
3044  float q1;
3045  float q2;
3046  float q3;
3047  float vn;
3048  float ve;
3049  float vd;
3050  float vwn;
3051  float vwe;
3052  const float R_BETA = 0.03f; // assume a sideslip angle RMS of ~10 deg
3053  Vector13 SH_BETA;
3054  Vector8 SK_BETA;
3055  Vector3f vel_rel_wind;
3056  Vector22 H_BETA;
3057  float innovBeta;
3058 
3059  // copy required states to local variable names
3060  q0 = state.quat[0];
3061  q1 = state.quat[1];
3062  q2 = state.quat[2];
3063  q3 = state.quat[3];
3064  vn = state.velocity.x;
3065  ve = state.velocity.y;
3066  vd = state.velocity.z;
3067  vwn = state.wind_vel.x;
3068  vwe = state.wind_vel.y;
3069 
3070  // calculate predicted wind relative velocity in NED
3071  vel_rel_wind.x = vn - vwn ;
3072  vel_rel_wind.y = ve - vwe;
3073  vel_rel_wind.z = vd;
3074 
3075  // rotate into body axes
3076  vel_rel_wind = prevTnb * vel_rel_wind;
3077 
3078  // perform fusion of assumed sideslip = 0
3079  if (vel_rel_wind.x > 5.0f)
3080  {
3081  // Calculate observation jacobians
3082  SH_BETA[0] = (vn - vwn)*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3)) - vd*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) + (ve - vwe)*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
3083  if (fabsf(SH_BETA[0]) <= 1e-9f) {
3084  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = true;
3085  return;
3086  } else {
3087  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = false;
3088  }
3089  SH_BETA[1] = (ve - vwe)*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3)) + vd*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) - (vn - vwn)*(2*q0*q3 - 2*q1*q2);
3090  SH_BETA[2] = vn - vwn;
3091  SH_BETA[3] = ve - vwe;
3092  SH_BETA[4] = 1/sq(SH_BETA[0]);
3093  SH_BETA[5] = 1/SH_BETA[0];
3094  SH_BETA[6] = SH_BETA[5]*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3));
3095  SH_BETA[7] = sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3);
3096  SH_BETA[8] = 2*q0*SH_BETA[3] - 2*q3*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q1*vd;
3097  SH_BETA[9] = 2*q0*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q3*SH_BETA[3] - 2*q2*vd;
3098  SH_BETA[10] = 2*q2*SH_BETA[2] - 2*q1*SH_BETA[3] + 2*q0*vd;
3099  SH_BETA[11] = 2*q1*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q2*SH_BETA[3] + 2*q3*vd;
3100  SH_BETA[12] = 2*q0*q3;
3101  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) {
3102  H_BETA[i] = 0.0f;
3103  }
3104  H_BETA[0] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9];
3105  H_BETA[1] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11];
3106  H_BETA[2] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10];
3107  H_BETA[3] = - SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8];
3108  H_BETA[4] = - SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];
3109  H_BETA[5] = SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2);
3110  H_BETA[6] = SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3);
3111  H_BETA[14] = SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];
3112  H_BETA[15] = SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2) - SH_BETA[6];
3113 
3114  // Calculate Kalman gains
3115  float temp = (R_BETA - (SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7])*(P[14][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) - P[4][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) + P[5][4]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) - P[15][4]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) + P[0][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9]) + P[1][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11]) + P[2][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10]) - P[3][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8]) + P[6][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3))) + (SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7])*(P[14][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) - P[4][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) + P[5][14]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) - P[15][14]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) + P[0][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9]) + P[1][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11]) + P[2][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10]) - P[3][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8]) + P[6][14]*(SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3))) + (SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2))*(P[14][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) - P[4][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) + P[5][5]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) - P[15][5]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) + P[0][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9]) + P[1][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11]) + P[2][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10]) - P[3][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8]) + P[6][5]*(SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3))) - (SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2))*(P[14][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) - P[4][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) + P[5][15]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) - P[15][15]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) + P[0][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9]) + P[1][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11]) + P[2][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10]) - P[3][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8]) + P[6][15]*(SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3))));
3116  if (temp >= R_BETA) {
3117  SK_BETA[0] = 1.0f / temp;
3118  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = false;
3119  } else {
3120  // the calculation is badly conditioned, so we cannot perform fusion on this step
3121  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = true;
3122  return;
3123  }
3124  SK_BETA[1] = SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];
3125  SK_BETA[2] = SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2);
3126  SK_BETA[3] = SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3);
3127  SK_BETA[4] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11];
3128  SK_BETA[5] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9];
3129  SK_BETA[6] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10];
3130  SK_BETA[7] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8];
3131  Kfusion[0] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[0][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[0][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[0][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[0][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[0][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[0][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[0][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[0][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[0][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3132  Kfusion[1] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[1][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[1][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[1][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[1][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[1][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[1][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[1][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[1][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[1][15]*SK_BETA[2]);

3134  Kfusion[3] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[3][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[3][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[3][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[3][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[3][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[3][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[3][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[3][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[3][15]*SK_BETA[2]);

3136  Kfusion[5] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[5][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[5][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[5][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[5][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[5][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[5][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[5][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[5][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[5][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3137  Kfusion[6] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[6][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[6][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[6][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[6][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[6][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[6][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[6][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[6][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[6][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3138  Kfusion[7] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[7][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[7][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[7][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[7][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[7][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[7][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[7][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[7][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[7][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3139  Kfusion[8] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[8][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[8][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[8][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[8][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[8][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[8][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[8][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[8][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[8][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3140  Kfusion[9] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[9][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[9][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[9][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[9][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[9][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[9][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[9][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[9][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[9][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3141  Kfusion[10] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[10][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[10][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[10][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[10][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[10][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[10][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[10][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[10][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[10][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3142  Kfusion[11] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[11][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[11][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[11][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[11][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[11][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[11][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[11][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[11][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[11][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3143  Kfusion[12] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[12][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[12][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[12][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[12][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[12][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[12][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[12][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[12][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[12][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3144  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
3145  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_BETA[0]*(P[13][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[13][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[13][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[13][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[13][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[13][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[13][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[13][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[13][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3146  Kfusion[14] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[14][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[14][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[14][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[14][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[14][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[14][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[14][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[14][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[14][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3147  Kfusion[15] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[15][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[15][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[15][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[15][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[15][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[15][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[15][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[15][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[15][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3148  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
3149  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
3150  Kfusion[16] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[16][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[16][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[16][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[16][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[16][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[16][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[16][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[16][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[16][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3151  Kfusion[17] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[17][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[17][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[17][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[17][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[17][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[17][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[17][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[17][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[17][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3152  Kfusion[18] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[18][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[18][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[18][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[18][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[18][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[18][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[18][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[18][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[18][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3153  Kfusion[19] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[19][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[19][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[19][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[19][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[19][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[19][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[19][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[19][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[19][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3154  Kfusion[20] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[20][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[20][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[20][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[20][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[20][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[20][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[20][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[20][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[20][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3155  Kfusion[21] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[21][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[21][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[21][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[21][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[21][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[21][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[21][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[21][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[21][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3156  } else {
3157  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
3158  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
3159  }
3160  }
3161 
3162  // calculate predicted sideslip angle and innovation using small angle approximation
3163  innovBeta = vel_rel_wind.y / vel_rel_wind.x;
3164 
3165  // reject measurement if greater than 3-sigma inconsistency
3166  if (innovBeta > 0.5f) {
3167  return;
3168  }
3169 
3170  // correct the state vector
3171  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
3172  {
3173  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovBeta;
3174  }
3175 
3176  state.quat.normalize();
3177 
3178  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
3179  // take advantage of the empty columns in H to reduce the
3180  // number of operations
3181  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3182  {
3183  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=6; j++)
3184  {
3185  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_BETA[j];
3186  }
3187  for (uint8_t j = 7; j<=13; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3188  for (uint8_t j = 14; j<=15; j++)
3189  {
3190  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_BETA[j];
3191  }
3192  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3193  }
3194  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3195  {
3196  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3197  {
3198  KHP[i][j] = 0;
3199  for (uint8_t k = 0; k<=6; k++)
3200  {
3201  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3202  }
3203  for (uint8_t k = 14; k<=15; k++)
3204  {
3205  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3206  }
3207  }
3208  }
3209  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3210  {
3211  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3212  {
3213  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
3214  }
3215  }
3216  }
3217 
3218  // force the covariance matrix to me symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
3219  ForceSymmetry();
3220  ConstrainVariances();
3221 
3222  // stop the performance timer
3223  hal.util->perf_end(_perf_FuseSideslip);
3224 }

3226 // zero specified range of rows in the state covariance matrix
3227 void NavEKF_core::zeroRows(Matrix22 &covMat, uint8_t first, uint8_t last)
3228 {
3229  uint8_t row;
3230  for (row=first; row<=last; row++)
3231  {
3232  memset(&covMat[row][0], 0, sizeof(covMat[0][0])*22);
3233  }
3234 }
3235 
3236 // zero specified range of columns in the state covariance matrix
3237 void NavEKF_core::zeroCols(Matrix22 &covMat, uint8_t first, uint8_t last)
3238 {
3239  uint8_t row;
3240  for (row=0; row<=21; row++)
3241  {
3242  memset(&covMat[row][first], 0, sizeof(covMat[0][0])*(1+last-first));
3243  }
3244 }

3246 // store states in a history array along with time stamp
3247 void NavEKF_core::StoreStates()
3248 {
3249  // Don't need to store states more often than every 10 msec
3250  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastStateStoreTime_ms >= 10) {
3251  lastStateStoreTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
3252  if (storeIndex > 49) {
3253  storeIndex = 0;
3254  }
3255  storedStates[storeIndex] = state;
3256  statetimeStamp[storeIndex] = lastStateStoreTime_ms;
3257  storeIndex = storeIndex + 1;
3258  }
3259 }
3260 
3261 // reset the stored state history and store the current state
3262 void NavEKF_core::StoreStatesReset()
3263 {
3264  // clear stored state history
3265  memset(&storedStates[0], 0, sizeof(storedStates));
3266  memset(&statetimeStamp[0], 0, sizeof(statetimeStamp));
3267  // store current state vector in first column
3268  storeIndex = 0;
3269  storedStates[storeIndex] = state;
3270  statetimeStamp[storeIndex] = imuSampleTime_ms;
3271  storeIndex = storeIndex + 1;
3272 }
3273 
3274 // recall state vector stored at closest time to the one specified by msec
3275 void NavEKF_core::RecallStates(state_elements &statesForFusion, uint32_t msec)
3276 {
3277  uint32_t timeDelta;
3278  uint32_t bestTimeDelta = 200;
3279  uint8_t bestStoreIndex = 0;
3280  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++)
3281  {
3282  timeDelta = msec - statetimeStamp[i];
3283  if (timeDelta < bestTimeDelta)
3284  {
3285  bestStoreIndex = i;
3286  bestTimeDelta = timeDelta;
3287  }
3288  }
3289  if (bestTimeDelta < 200) // only output stored state if < 200 msec retrieval error
3290  {
3291  statesForFusion = storedStates[bestStoreIndex];
3292  }
3293  else // otherwise output current state
3294  {
3295  statesForFusion = state;
3296  }
3297 }

3299 // recall omega (angular rate vector) average across the time interval from msecStart to msecEnd
3300 void NavEKF_core::RecallOmega(Vector3f &omegaAvg, uint32_t msecStart, uint32_t msecEnd)
3301 {
3302  // calculate average angular rate vector over the time interval from msecStart to msecEnd
3303  // if no values are inside the time window, return the current angular rate
3304  omegaAvg.zero();
3305  uint8_t numAvg = 0;
3306  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++)
3307  {
3308  if (msecStart <= statetimeStamp[i] && msecEnd >= statetimeStamp[i])
3309  {
3310  omegaAvg += storedStates[i].omega;
3311  numAvg += 1;
3312  }
3313  }
3314  if (numAvg >= 1)
3315  {
3316  omegaAvg = omegaAvg / float(numAvg);
3317  } else if (dtDelAng > 0) {
3318  omegaAvg = correctedDelAng / dtDelAng;
3319  } else {
3320  omegaAvg.zero();
3321  }
3322 }

3358 // Return the last calculated NED position relative to the reference point (m).
3359 // if a calculated solution is not available, use the best available data and return false
3360 bool NavEKF_core::getPosNED(Vector3f &pos) const
3361 {
3362  // The EKF always has a height estimate regardless of mode of operation
3363  pos.z = state.position.z;
3364  // There are three modes of operation, absolute position (GPS fusion), relative position (optical flow fusion) and constant position (no position estimate available)
3365  nav_filter_status status;
3366  getFilterStatus(status);
3367  if (status.flags.horiz_pos_abs || status.flags.horiz_pos_rel) {
3368  // This is the normal mode of operation where we can use the EKF position states
3369  pos.x = state.position.x;
3370  pos.y = state.position.y;
3371  return true;
3372  } else {
3373  // In constant position mode the EKF position states are at the origin, so we cannot use them as a position estimate
3374  if(validOrigin) {
3375  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_2D)) {
3376  // If the origin has been set and we have GPS, then return the GPS position relative to the origin
3377  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3378  Vector2f tempPosNE = location_diff(EKF_origin, gpsloc);
3379  pos.x = tempPosNE.x;
3380  pos.y = tempPosNE.y;
3381  return false;
3382  } else {
3383  // If no GPS fix is available, all we can do is provide the last known position
3384  pos.x = state.position.x + lastKnownPositionNE.x;
3385  pos.y = state.position.y + lastKnownPositionNE.y;
3386  return false;
3387  }
3388  } else {
3389  // If the origin has not been set, then we have no means of providing a relative position
3390  pos.x = 0.0f;
3391  pos.y = 0.0f;
3392  return false;
3393  }
3394  }
3395  return false;
3396 }

3408 // reset the body axis gyro bias states to zero and re-initialise the corresponding covariances
3409 void NavEKF_core::resetGyroBias(void)
3410 {
3411  state.gyro_bias.zero();
3412  zeroRows(P,10,12);
3413  zeroCols(P,10,12);
3414  P[10][10] = sq(radians(InitialGyroBiasUncertainty() * dtIMUavg));
3415  P[11][11] = P[10][10];
3416  P[12][12] = P[10][10];
3417 
3418 }

3420 // Reset the baro so that it reads zero at the current height
3421 // Reset the EKF height to zero
3422 // Adjust the EKf origin height so that the EKF height + origin height is the same as before
3423 // Return true if the height datum reset has been performed
3424 // If using a range finder for height do not reset and return false
3425 bool NavEKF_core::resetHeightDatum(void)
3426 {
3427  // if we are using a range finder for height, return false
3428  if (frontend._altSource == 1) {
3429  return false;
3430  }
3431  // record the old height estimate
3432  float oldHgt = -state.position.z;
3433  // reset the barometer so that it reads zero at the current height
3434  _baro.update_calibration();
3435  // reset the height state
3436  state.position.z = 0.0f;
3437  // reset the stored height states from previous time steps
3438  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
3439  storedStates[i].position.z = state.position.z;
3440  }
3441  // adjust the height of the EKF origin so that the origin plus baro height before and afer the reset is the same
3442  if (validOrigin) {
3443  EKF_origin.alt += oldHgt*100;
3444  }
3445  return true;
3446 }

3452 // Returns 1 if attitude, vertical velocity and vertical position will be provided

3454 uint8_t NavEKF_core::setInhibitGPS(void)

3464  }

3467 // return the horizontal speed limit in m/s set by optical flow sensor limits
3468 // return the scale factor to be applied to navigation velocity gains to compensate for increase in velocity noise with height when using optical flow
3469 void NavEKF_core::getEkfControlLimits(float &ekfGndSpdLimit, float &ekfNavVelGainScaler) const
3470 {
3471  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) {
3472  // allow 1.0 rad/sec margin for angular motion
3473  ekfGndSpdLimit = max((frontend._maxFlowRate - 1.0f), 0.0f) * max((terrainState - state.position[2]), rngOnGnd);
3474  // use standard gains up to 5.0 metres height and reduce above that
3475  ekfNavVelGainScaler = 4.0f / max((terrainState - state.position[2]),4.0f);
3476  } else {
3477  ekfGndSpdLimit = 400.0f; //return 80% of max filter speed
3478  ekfNavVelGainScaler = 1.0f;
3479  }
3480 }

3519 // return magnetometer offsets

3533 // Return the last calculated latitude, longitude and height in WGS-84
3534 // If a calculated location isn't available, return a raw GPS measurement
3535 // The status will return true if a calculation or raw measurement is available
3536 // The getFilterStatus() function provides a more detailed description of data health and must be checked if data is to be used for flight control
3537 bool NavEKF_core::getLLH(struct Location &loc) const
3538 {
3539  if(validOrigin) {
3540  // Altitude returned is an absolute altitude relative to the WGS-84 spherioid
3541  loc.alt = EKF_origin.alt - state.position.z*100;
3542  loc.flags.relative_alt = 0;
3543  loc.flags.terrain_alt = 0;
3544 
3545  // there are three modes of operation, absolute position (GPS fusion), relative position (optical flow fusion) and constant position (no aiding)
3546  nav_filter_status status;
3547  getFilterStatus(status);
3548  if (status.flags.horiz_pos_abs || status.flags.horiz_pos_rel) {
3549  loc.lat = EKF_origin.lat;
3550  loc.lng = EKF_origin.lng;
3551  location_offset(loc, state.position.x, state.position.y);
3552  return true;
3553  } else {
3554  // we could be in constant position mode becasue the vehicle has taken off without GPS, or has lost GPS
3555  // in this mode we cannot use the EKF states to estimate position so will return the best available data
3556  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_2D)) {
3557  // we have a GPS position fix to return
3558  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3559  loc.lat = gpsloc.lat;
3560  loc.lng = gpsloc.lng;
3561  return true;
3562  } else {
3563  // if no GPS fix, provide last known position before entering the mode
3564  location_offset(loc, lastKnownPositionNE.x, lastKnownPositionNE.y);
3565  return false;
3566  }
3567  }
3568  } else {
3569  // If no origin has been defined for the EKF, then we cannot use its position states so return a raw
3570  // GPS reading if available and return false
3571  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D)) {
3572  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3573  loc = gpsloc;
3574  loc.flags.relative_alt = 0;
3575  loc.flags.terrain_alt = 0;
3576  }
3577  return false;
3578  }
3579 }

3584  HAGL = terrainState - state.position.z;

3590 void NavEKF_core::getFlowDebug(float &varFlow, float &gndOffset, float &flowInnovX, float &flowInnovY, float &auxInnov, float &HAGL, float &rngInnov, float &range, float &gndOffsetErr) const

3602 
3603 // calculate whether the flight vehicle is on the ground or flying from height, airspeed and GPS speed
3604 void NavEKF_core::SetFlightAndFusionModes()
3605 {
3606  // determine if the vehicle is manoevring
3607  if (accNavMagHoriz > 0.5f){
3608  manoeuvring = true;
3609  } else {
3610  manoeuvring = false;
3611  }
3612  // if we are a fly forward type vehicle, then in-air mode can be determined through a combination of speed and height criteria
3613  if (assume_zero_sideslip()) {
3614  // Evaluate a numerical score that defines the likelihood we are in the air
3615  float gndSpdSq = sq(velNED[0]) + sq(velNED[1]);
3616  bool highGndSpd = false;
3617  bool highAirSpd = false;
3618  bool largeHgtChange = false;
3619 
3620  // trigger at 8 m/s airspeed
3621  if (_ahrs->airspeed_sensor_enabled()) {
3622  const AP_Airspeed *airspeed = _ahrs->get_airspeed();
3623  if (airspeed->get_airspeed() * airspeed->get_EAS2TAS() > 10.0f) {
3624  highAirSpd = true;
3625  }
3626  }
3627 
3628  // trigger at 10 m/s GPS velocity, but not if GPS is reporting bad velocity errors
3629  if (gndSpdSq > 100.0f && gpsSpdAccuracy < 1.0f) {
3630  highGndSpd = true;
3631  }
3632 
3633  // trigger if more than 10m away from initial height
3634  if (fabsf(hgtMea) > 10.0f) {
3635  largeHgtChange = true;
3636  }
3637 
3638  // to go to in-air mode we also need enough GPS velocity to be able to calculate a reliable ground track heading and either a lerge height or airspeed change
3639  if (onGround && highGndSpd && (highAirSpd || largeHgtChange)) {
3640  onGround = false;
3641  }
3642  // if is possible we are in flight, set the time this condition was last detected
3643  if (highGndSpd || highAirSpd || largeHgtChange) {
3644  airborneDetectTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
3645  }
3646  // after 5 seconds of not detecting a possible flight condition, we transition to on-ground mode
3647  if(!onGround && ((imuSampleTime_ms - airborneDetectTime_ms) > 5000)) {
3648  onGround = true;
3649  }
3650  // perform a yaw alignment check against GPS if exiting on-ground mode, bu tonly if we have enough ground speed
3651  // this is done to protect against unrecoverable heading alignment errors due to compass faults
3652  if (!onGround && prevOnGround) {
3653  alignYawGPS();
3654  }
3655  // If we aren't using an airspeed sensor we set the wind velocity to the reciprocal
3656  // of the velocity vector and scale states so that the wind speed is equal to 3m/s. This helps prevent gains
3657  // being too high at the start of flight if launching into a headwind until the first turn when the EKF can form
3658  // a wind speed estimate and also corrects bad initial wind estimates due to heading errors
3659  if (!onGround && prevOnGround && !useAirspeed()) {
3660  setWindVelStates();
3661  }
3662  }
3663  // store current on-ground status for next time
3664  prevOnGround = onGround;
3665  // If we are on ground, or in constant position mode, or don't have the right vehicle and sensing to estimate wind, inhibit wind states
3666  inhibitWindStates = ((!useAirspeed() && !assume_zero_sideslip()) || onGround || constPosMode);
3667  // request mag calibration for both in-air and manoeuvre threshold options
3668  bool magCalRequested = ((frontend._magCal == 0) && !onGround) || ((frontend._magCal == 1) && manoeuvring) || (frontend._magCal == 3);
3669  // deny mag calibration request if we aren't using the compass, are in the pre-arm constant position mode or it has been inhibited by the user
3670  bool magCalDenied = !use_compass() || constPosMode || (frontend._magCal == 2);
3671  // inhibit the magnetic field calibration if not requested or denied
3672  inhibitMagStates = (!magCalRequested || magCalDenied);
3673 }
3674 
3675 // initialise the covariance matrix
3676 void NavEKF_core::CovarianceInit()
3677 {
3678  // zero the matrix
3679  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++)
3680  {
3681  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
3682  {
3683  P[i][j] = 0.0f;
3684  }
3685  }
3686  // quaternions - TODO better maths for initial quaternion covariances that uses roll, pitch and yaw
3687  P[0][0] = 1.0e-9f;
3688  P[1][1] = 0.25f*sq(radians(10.0f));
3689  P[2][2] = 0.25f*sq(radians(10.0f));
3690  P[3][3] = 0.25f*sq(radians(10.0f));
3691  // velocities
3692  P[4][4] = sq(0.7f);
3693  P[5][5] = P[4][4];
3694  P[6][6] = sq(0.7f);
3695  // positions
3696  P[7][7] = sq(15.0f);
3697  P[8][8] = P[7][7];
3698  P[9][9] = sq(frontend._baroAltNoise);
3699  // delta angle biases
3700  P[10][10] = sq(radians(InitialGyroBiasUncertainty() * dtIMUavg));
3701  P[11][11] = P[10][10];
3702  P[12][12] = P[10][10];
3703  // Z delta velocity bias
3704  P[13][13] = sq(INIT_ACCEL_BIAS_UNCERTAINTY * dtIMUavg);
3705  // wind velocities
3706  P[14][14] = 0.0f;
3707  P[15][15] = P[14][14];
3708  // earth magnetic field
3709  P[16][16] = 0.0f;
3710  P[17][17] = P[16][16];
3711  P[18][18] = P[16][16];
3712  // body magnetic field
3713  P[19][19] = 0.0f;
3714  P[20][20] = P[19][19];
3715  P[21][21] = P[19][19];
3716 
3717  // optical flow ground height covariance
3718  Popt = 0.25f;
3719 
3720 }
3721 
3722 // force symmetry on the covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
3723 void NavEKF_core::ForceSymmetry()
3724 {
3725  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++)
3726  {
3727  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=i-1; j++)
3728  {
3729  float temp = 0.5f*(P[i][j] + P[j][i]);
3730  P[i][j] = temp;
3731  P[j][i] = temp;
3732  }
3733  }
3734 }
3735 
3736 // copy covariances across from covariance prediction calculation and fix numerical errors
3737 void NavEKF_core::CopyAndFixCovariances()
3738 {
3739  // copy predicted variances
3740  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) {
3741  P[i][i] = nextP[i][i];
3742  }
3743  // copy predicted covariances and force symmetry
3744  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++) {
3745  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=i-1; j++)
3746  {
3747  P[i][j] = 0.5f*(nextP[i][j] + nextP[j][i]);
3748  P[j][i] = P[i][j];
3749  }
3750  }
3751 }
3752 
3753 // constrain variances (diagonal terms) in the state covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
3754 void NavEKF_core::ConstrainVariances()
3755 {
3756  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0f); // quaternions
3757  for (uint8_t i=4; i<=6; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e3f); // velocities
3758  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=9; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e6f); // positions
3759  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,sq(0.175f * dtIMUavg)); // delta angle biases
3760  P[13][13] = constrain_float(P[13][13],0.0f,sq(10.0f * dtIMUavg)); // delta velocity bias
3761  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e3f); // earth magnetic field
3762  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0f); // body magnetic field
3763 }
3764 
3765 // constrain states to prevent ill-conditioning
3766 void NavEKF_core::ConstrainStates()
3767 {
3768  // quaternions are limited between +-1
3769  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
3770  // velocity limit 500 m/sec (could set this based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS)
3771  for (uint8_t i=4; i<=6; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-5.0e2f,5.0e2f);
3772  // position limit 1000 km - TODO apply circular limit
3773  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0e6f,1.0e6f);
3774  // height limit covers home alt on everest through to home alt at SL and ballon drop
3775  state.position.z = constrain_float(state.position.z,-4.0e4f,1.0e4f);
3776  // gyro bias limit ~6 deg/sec (this needs to be set based on manufacturers specs)
3777  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-0.1f*dtIMUavg,0.1f*dtIMUavg);
3778  // when the vehicle arms we adjust the limits so that in flight the bias can change by the same amount in either direction
3779  float delAngBiasLim = MAX_GYRO_BIAS*dtIMUavg;
3780  state.gyro_bias.x = constrain_float(state.gyro_bias.x, (delAngBiasAtArming.x - delAngBiasLim), (delAngBiasAtArming.x + delAngBiasLim));
3781  state.gyro_bias.y = constrain_float(state.gyro_bias.y, (delAngBiasAtArming.y - delAngBiasLim), (delAngBiasAtArming.y + delAngBiasLim));
3782  state.gyro_bias.z = constrain_float(state.gyro_bias.z, (delAngBiasAtArming.z - delAngBiasLim), (delAngBiasAtArming.z + delAngBiasLim));
3783  // Z accel bias limit 1.0 m/s^2 (this needs to be finalised from test data)
3784  states[13] = constrain_float(states[13],-1.0f*dtIMUavg,1.0f*dtIMUavg);
3785  states[22] = constrain_float(states[22],-1.0f*dtIMUavg,1.0f*dtIMUavg);
3786  // wind velocity limit 100 m/s (could be based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS) - TODO apply circular limit
3787  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-100.0f,100.0f);
3788  // earth magnetic field limit
3789  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
3790  // body magnetic field limit
3791  for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-0.5f,0.5f);
3792  // constrain the terrain offset state
3793  terrainState = max(terrainState, state.position.z + rngOnGnd);
3794 }

3800  ins.get_delta_velocity(ins_index,dVel);
3801  dVel_dt = ins.get_delta_velocity_dt(ins_index);
3802  return true;
3803  }
3804  return false;

3817 // update IMU delta angle and delta velocity measurements
3818 void NavEKF_core::readIMUData()
3819 {
3820  const AP_InertialSensor &ins = _ahrs->get_ins();
3821 
3822  dtIMUavg = 1.0f/ins.get_sample_rate();
3823  dtDelAng = max(ins.get_delta_time(),1.0e-4f);
3824 
3825  // the imu sample time is used as a common time reference throughout the filter
3826  imuSampleTime_ms = hal.scheduler->millis();
3827 
3828  // dual accel mode - require both IMU's to be able to provide delta velocity outputs
3829  if (ins.use_accel(0) && ins.use_accel(1) && readDeltaVelocity(0, dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1) && readDeltaVelocity(1, dVelIMU2, dtDelVel2)) {
3830 
3831  // apply a peak hold 0.2 second time constant decaying envelope filter to the noise length on IMU1
3832  float alpha = 1.0f - 5.0f*dtDelVel1;
3833  imuNoiseFiltState1 = maxf(ins.get_vibration_levels(0).length(), alpha*imuNoiseFiltState1);
3834 
3835  // apply a peak hold 0.2 second time constant decaying envelope filter to the noise length on IMU2
3836  alpha = 1.0f - 5.0f*dtDelVel2;
3837  imuNoiseFiltState2 = maxf(ins.get_vibration_levels(1).length(), alpha*imuNoiseFiltState2);
3838 
3839  // calculate the filtered difference between acceleration vectors from IMU1 and 2
3840  // apply a LPF filter with a 1.0 second time constant
3841  alpha = constrain_float(0.5f*(dtDelVel1 + dtDelVel2),0.0f,1.0f);
3842  accelDiffFilt = (ins.get_accel(0) - ins.get_accel(1)) * alpha + accelDiffFilt * (1.0f - alpha);
3843  float accelDiffLength = accelDiffFilt.length();
3844 
3845  // Check the difference for excessive error and use the IMU with less noise
3846  // Apply hysteresis to prevent rapid switching
3847  if (accelDiffLength > 1.8f || (accelDiffLength > 1.2f && lastImuSwitchState != IMUSWITCH_MIXED)) {
3848  if (lastImuSwitchState == IMUSWITCH_MIXED) {
3849  // no previous fail so switch to the IMU with least noise
3850  if (imuNoiseFiltState1 < imuNoiseFiltState2) {
3851  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU0;
3852  } else {
3853  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU1;
3854  }
3855  } else if (lastImuSwitchState == IMUSWITCH_IMU0) {
3856  // IMU1 previously failed so require 5 m/s/s less noise on IMU2 to switch across
3857  if (imuNoiseFiltState1 - imuNoiseFiltState2 > 5.0f) {
3858  // IMU2 is significantly less noisy, so switch
3859  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU1;
3860  }
3861  } else {
3862  // IMU2 previously failed so require 5 m/s/s less noise on IMU1 to switch across
3863  if (imuNoiseFiltState2 - imuNoiseFiltState1 > 5.0f) {
3864  // IMU1 is significantly less noisy, so switch
3865  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU0;
3866  }
3867  }
3868  } else {
3869  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_MIXED;
3870  }
3871 
3872  } else {
3873  // single accel mode - one of the first two accelerometers are unhealthy, not available or de-selected by the user
3874  // read good accelerometer into dVelIMU1 and copy to dVelIMU2
3875  // set the switch state based on the IMU we are using to make the data source selection visible
3876  if (ins.use_accel(0) && readDeltaVelocity(0, dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1)) {
3877  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU0;
3878  } else if (ins.use_accel(1) && readDeltaVelocity(1, dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1)) {
3879  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU1;
3880  } else {
3881  readDeltaVelocity(ins.get_primary_accel(), dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1);
3882  switch (ins.get_primary_accel()) {
3883  case 0:
3884  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU0;
3885  break;
3886  case 1:
3887  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_IMU1;
3888  break;
3889  default:
3890  // we must be using IMU2 which can't be properly represented so we set to "mixed"
3891  lastImuSwitchState = IMUSWITCH_MIXED;
3892  break;
3893  }
3894  }
3895  dtDelVel2 = dtDelVel1;
3896  dVelIMU2 = dVelIMU1;
3897  }
3898 
3899  // Default is to use the average of two gyros if available
3900  // This reduces rate offset due to temperature variation
3901  Vector3f dAng0,dAng1;
3902  if (ins.use_gyro(0) && ins.use_gyro(1) && readDeltaAngle(0, dAng0) && readDeltaAngle(1, dAng1)) {
3903  dAngIMU = (dAng0+dAng1);
3904  dAngIMU *= 0.5f;
3905  } else {
3906  // single gyro mode - one of the first two gyros are unhealthy or don't exist
3907  // just read primary gyro
3908  readDeltaAngle(ins.get_primary_gyro(), dAngIMU);
3909  }
3910 }
