3912 // check for new valid GPS data and update stored measurement if available
3913 void NavEKF_core::readGpsData()
3914 {
3915  // check for new GPS data
3916  if (_ahrs->get_gps().last_message_time_ms() != lastFixTime_ms) {
3917  if (_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
3918  // report GPS fix status
3919  gpsCheckStatus.bad_fix = false;
3920 
3921  // store fix time from previous read
3922  secondLastFixTime_ms = lastFixTime_ms;
3923 
3924  // get current fix time
3925  lastFixTime_ms = _ahrs->get_gps().last_message_time_ms();
3926 
3927  // set flag that lets other functions know that new GPS data has arrived
3928  newDataGps = true;
3929 
3930  // get state vectors that were stored at the time that is closest to when the the GPS measurement
3931  // time after accounting for measurement delays
3932  RecallStates(statesAtVelTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - constrain_int16(frontend._msecVelDelay, 0, 500)));
3933  RecallStates(statesAtPosTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - constrain_int16(frontend._msecPosDelay, 0, 500)));
3934 
3935  // read the NED velocity from the GPS
3936  velNED = _ahrs->get_gps().velocity();
3937 
3938  // Use the speed accuracy from the GPS if available, otherwise set it to zero.
3939  // Apply a decaying envelope filter with a 5 second time constant to the raw speed accuracy data
3940  float alpha = constrain_float(0.0002f * (lastFixTime_ms - secondLastFixTime_ms),0.0f,1.0f);
3941  gpsSpdAccuracy *= (1.0f - alpha);
3942  float gpsSpdAccRaw;
3943  if (!_ahrs->get_gps().speed_accuracy(gpsSpdAccRaw)) {
3944  gpsSpdAccuracy = 0.0f;
3945  } else {
3946  gpsSpdAccuracy = max(gpsSpdAccuracy,gpsSpdAccRaw);
3947  }
3948 
3949  // check if we have enough GPS satellites and increase the gps noise scaler if we don't
3950  if (_ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() >= 6 && !constPosMode) {
3951  gpsNoiseScaler = 1.0f;
3952  } else if (_ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() == 5 && !constPosMode) {
3953  gpsNoiseScaler = 1.4f;
3954  } else { // <= 4 satellites or in constant position mode
3955  gpsNoiseScaler = 2.0f;
3956  }
3957 
3958  // Check if GPS can output vertical velocity and set GPS fusion mode accordingly
3959  if (_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity() && frontend._fusionModeGPS == 0) {
3960  useGpsVertVel = true;
3961  } else {
3962  useGpsVertVel = false;
3963  }
3964 
3965  // Monitor quality of the GPS velocity data for alignment
3966  gpsGoodToAlign = calcGpsGoodToAlign();
3967 
3968  // Monitor qulaity of GPS data inflight
3969  calcGpsGoodForFlight();
3970 
3971  // Read the GPS locaton in WGS-84 lat,long,height coordinates
3972  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3973 
3974  // Set the EKF origin and magnetic field declination if not previously set and GPS checks have passed
3975  if (!validOrigin && gpsGoodToAlign) {
3976  setOrigin();
3977  // Now we know the location we have an estimate for the magnetic field declination and adjust the earth field accordingly
3978  alignMagStateDeclination();
3979  // Set the height of the NED origin to ‘height of baro height datum relative to GPS height datum'
3980  EKF_origin.alt = gpsloc.alt - hgtMea;
3981  }
3982 
3983  // Commence GPS aiding when able to
3984  if ((frontend._fusionModeGPS != 3) && (PV_AidingMode != AID_ABSOLUTE) && vehicleArmed && gpsGoodToAlign) {
3985  PV_AidingMode = AID_ABSOLUTE;
3986  constPosMode = false;
3987  // Initialise EKF position and velocity states to last GPS measurement
3988  ResetPosition();
3989  ResetVelocity();
3990  }
3991 
3992  // Convert to local coordinates if we have an origin.
3993  if (validOrigin) {
3994  gpsPosNE = location_diff(EKF_origin, gpsloc);
3995  }
3996  } else {
3997  // report GPS fix status
3998  gpsCheckStatus.bad_fix = true;
3999  }
4000  }
4001 
4002 
4003  // If no previous GPS lock or told not to use it, or EKF origin not set, we declare the GPS unavailable for use
4004  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) || frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3 || !validOrigin) {
4005  gpsNotAvailable = true;
4006  } else {
4007  gpsNotAvailable = false;
4008  }
4009 }

4011 // check for new altitude measurement data and update stored measurement if available
4012 void NavEKF_core::readHgtData()
4013 {
4014  // check to see if baro measurement has changed so we know if a new measurement has arrived
4015  if (_baro.healthy() && _baro.get_last_update() != lastHgtMeasTime) {
4016  // Don't use Baro height if operating in optical flow mode as we use range finder instead
4017  if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3 && frontend._altSource == 1) {
4018  if ((imuSampleTime_ms - rngValidMeaTime_ms) < 2000) {
4019  // adjust range finder measurement to allow for effect of vehicle tilt and height of sensor
4020  hgtMea = max(rngMea * Tnb_flow.c.z, rngOnGnd);
4021  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4022  statesAtHgtTime = statesAtFlowTime;
4023  // calculate offset to baro data that enables baro to be used as a backup
4024  // filter offset to reduce effect of baro noise and other transient errors on estimate
4025  baroHgtOffset = 0.1f * (_baro.get_altitude() + state.position.z) + 0.9f * baroHgtOffset;
4026  } else if (vehicleArmed && takeOffDetected) {
4027  // use baro measurement and correct for baro offset - failsafe use only as baro will drift
4028  hgtMea = max(_baro.get_altitude() - baroHgtOffset, rngOnGnd);
4029  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4030  RecallStates(statesAtHgtTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecHgtDelay));
4031  } else {
4032  // If we are on ground and have no range finder reading, assume the nominal on-ground height
4033  hgtMea = rngOnGnd;
4034  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4035  statesAtHgtTime = state;
4036  // calculate offset to baro data that enables baro to be used as a backup
4037  // filter offset to reduce effect of baro noise and other transient errors on estimate
4038  baroHgtOffset = 0.1f * (_baro.get_altitude() + state.position.z) + 0.9f * baroHgtOffset;
4039  }
4040  } else {
4041  // use baro measurement and correct for baro offset
4042  hgtMea = _baro.get_altitude();
4043  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4044  RecallStates(statesAtHgtTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecHgtDelay));
4045  }
4046 
4047  // filtered baro data used to provide a reference for takeoff
4048  // it is is reset to last height measurement on disarming in performArmingChecks()
4049  if (!getTakeoffExpected()) {
4050  static const float gndHgtFiltTC = 0.5f;
4051  static const float dtBaro = msecHgtAvg*1.0e-3f;
4052  float alpha = constrain_float(dtBaro / (dtBaro+gndHgtFiltTC),0.0f,1.0f);
4053  meaHgtAtTakeOff += (hgtMea-meaHgtAtTakeOff)*alpha;
4054  } else if (vehicleArmed && getTakeoffExpected()) {
4055  // If we are in takeoff mode, the height measurement is limited to be no less than the measurement at start of takeoff
4056  // This prevents negative baro disturbances due to copter downwash corrupting the EKF altitude during initial ascent
4057  hgtMea = max(hgtMea, meaHgtAtTakeOff);
4058  }
4059 
4060  // set flag to let other functions know new data has arrived
4061  newDataHgt = true;
4062  // time stamp used to check for new measurement
4063  lastHgtMeasTime = _baro.get_last_update();
4064  } else {
4065  newDataHgt = false;
4066  }
4067 }

4069 // check for new magnetometer data and update store measurements if available
4070 void NavEKF_core::readMagData()
4071 {
4072  if (use_compass() && _ahrs->get_compass()->last_update_usec() != lastMagUpdate) {
4073  // store time of last measurement update
4074  lastMagUpdate = _ahrs->get_compass()->last_update_usec();
4075 
4076  // read compass data and scale to improve numerical conditioning
4077  magData = _ahrs->get_compass()->get_field() * 0.001f;
4078 
4079  // check for consistent data between magnetometers
4080  consistentMagData = _ahrs->get_compass()->consistent();
4081 
4082  // get states stored at time closest to measurement time after allowance for measurement delay
4083  RecallStates(statesAtMagMeasTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecMagDelay));
4084 
4085  // let other processes know that new compass data has arrived
4086  newDataMag = true;
4087 
4088  // check if compass offsets have ben changed and adjust EKF bias states to maintain consistent innovations
4089  if (_ahrs->get_compass()->healthy()) {
4090  Vector3f nowMagOffsets = _ahrs->get_compass()->get_offsets();
4091  bool changeDetected = (!is_equal(nowMagOffsets.x,lastMagOffsets.x) || !is_equal(nowMagOffsets.y,lastMagOffsets.y) || !is_equal(nowMagOffsets.z,lastMagOffsets.z));
4092  // Ignore bias changes before final mag field and yaw initialisation, as there may have been a compass calibration
4093  if (changeDetected && secondMagYawInit) {
4094  state.body_magfield.x += (nowMagOffsets.x - lastMagOffsets.x) * 0.001f;
4095  state.body_magfield.y += (nowMagOffsets.y - lastMagOffsets.y) * 0.001f;
4096  state.body_magfield.z += (nowMagOffsets.z - lastMagOffsets.z) * 0.001f;
4097  }
4098  lastMagOffsets = nowMagOffsets;
4099  }
4100  } else {
4101  newDataMag = false;
4102  }
4103 }

4124 // write the raw optical flow measurements
4125 // this needs to be called externally.
4126 void NavEKF_core::writeOptFlowMeas(uint8_t &rawFlowQuality, Vector2f &rawFlowRates, Vector2f &rawGyroRates, uint32_t &msecFlowMeas)
4127 {
4128  // The raw measurements need to be optical flow rates in radians/second averaged across the time since the last update
4129  // The PX4Flow sensor outputs flow rates with the following axis and sign conventions:
4130  // A positive X rate is produced by a positive sensor rotation about the X axis
4131  // A positive Y rate is produced by a positive sensor rotation about the Y axis
4132  // This filter uses a different definition of optical flow rates to the sensor with a positive optical flow rate produced by a
4133  // negative rotation about that axis. For example a positive rotation of the flight vehicle about its X (roll) axis would produce a negative X flow rate
4134  flowMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4135  flowQuality = rawFlowQuality;
4136  // recall angular rates averaged across flow observation period allowing for processing, transmission and intersample delays
4137  RecallOmega(omegaAcrossFlowTime, imuSampleTime_ms - flowTimeDeltaAvg_ms - frontend._msecFLowDelay, imuSampleTime_ms - frontend._msecFLowDelay);
4138  // calculate bias errors on flow sensor gyro rates, but protect against spikes in data
4139  flowGyroBias.x = 0.99f * flowGyroBias.x + 0.01f * constrain_float((rawGyroRates.x - omegaAcrossFlowTime.x),-0.1f,0.1f);
4140  flowGyroBias.y = 0.99f * flowGyroBias.y + 0.01f * constrain_float((rawGyroRates.y - omegaAcrossFlowTime.y),-0.1f,0.1f);
4141  // check for takeoff if relying on optical flow and zero measurements until takeoff detected
4142  // if we haven't taken off - constrain position and velocity states
4143  if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3) {
4144  detectOptFlowTakeoff();
4145  }
4146  // recall vehicle states at mid sample time for flow observations allowing for delays
4147  RecallStates(statesAtFlowTime, imuSampleTime_ms - frontend._msecFLowDelay - flowTimeDeltaAvg_ms/2);
4148  // calculate rotation matrices at mid sample time for flow observations
4149  statesAtFlowTime.quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn_flow);
4150  Tnb_flow = Tbn_flow.transposed();
4151  // don't use data with a low quality indicator or extreme rates (helps catch corrupt sensor data)
4152  if ((rawFlowQuality > 0) && rawFlowRates.length() < 4.2f && rawGyroRates.length() < 4.2f) {
4153  // correct flow sensor rates for bias
4154  omegaAcrossFlowTime.x = rawGyroRates.x - flowGyroBias.x;
4155  omegaAcrossFlowTime.y = rawGyroRates.y - flowGyroBias.y;
4156  // write uncorrected flow rate measurements that will be used by the focal length scale factor estimator
4157  // note correction for different axis and sign conventions used by the px4flow sensor
4158  flowRadXY[0] = - rawFlowRates.x; // raw (non motion compensated) optical flow angular rate about the X axis (rad/sec)
4159  flowRadXY[1] = - rawFlowRates.y; // raw (non motion compensated) optical flow angular rate about the Y axis (rad/sec)
4160  // write flow rate measurements corrected for body rates
4161  flowRadXYcomp[0] = flowRadXY[0] + omegaAcrossFlowTime.x;
4162  flowRadXYcomp[1] = flowRadXY[1] + omegaAcrossFlowTime.y;
4163  // set flag that will trigger observations
4164  newDataFlow = true;
4165  flowValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4166  } else {
4167  newDataFlow = false;
4168  }
4169 }
4170 
4171 // calculate the NED earth spin vector in rad/sec
4172 void NavEKF_core::calcEarthRateNED(Vector3f &omega, int32_t latitude) const
4173 {
4174  float lat_rad = radians(latitude*1.0e-7f);
4175  omega.x = earthRate*cosf(lat_rad);
4176  omega.y = 0;
4177  omega.z = -earthRate*sinf(lat_rad);
4178 }
4179 
4180 // initialise the earth magnetic field states using declination, suppled roll/pitch
4181 // and magnetometer measurements and return initial attitude quaternion
4182 // if no magnetometer data, do not update magnetic field states and assume zero yaw angle
4183 Quaternion NavEKF_core::calcQuatAndFieldStates(float roll, float pitch)
4184 {
4185  // declare local variables required to calculate initial orientation and magnetic field
4186  float yaw;
4187  Matrix3f Tbn;
4188  Vector3f initMagNED;
4189  Quaternion initQuat;
4190 
4191  if (use_compass()) {
4192  // calculate rotation matrix from body to NED frame
4193  Tbn.from_euler(roll, pitch, 0.0f);
4194 
4195  // read the magnetometer data
4196  readMagData();
4197 
4198  // rotate the magnetic field into NED axes
4199  initMagNED = Tbn * magData;
4200 
4201  // calculate heading of mag field rel to body heading
4202  float magHeading = atan2f(initMagNED.y, initMagNED.x);
4203 
4204  // get the magnetic declination
4205  float magDecAng = use_compass() ? _ahrs->get_compass()->get_declination() : 0;
4206 
4207  // calculate yaw angle rel to true north
4208  yaw = magDecAng - magHeading;
4209  yawAligned = true;
4210  // calculate initial filter quaternion states using yaw from magnetometer if mag heading healthy
4211  // otherwise use existing heading
4212  if (!badMag) {
4213  // store the yaw change so that it can be retrieved externally for use by the control loops to prevent yaw disturbances following a reset
4214  Vector3f tempEuler;
4215  state.quat.to_euler(tempEuler.x, tempEuler.y, tempEuler.z);
4216  // this check ensures we accumulate the resets that occur within a single iteration of the EKF
4217  if (imuSampleTime_ms != lastYawReset_ms) {
4218  yawResetAngle = 0.0f;
4219  }
4220  yawResetAngle += wrap_PI(yaw - tempEuler.z);
4221  lastYawReset_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4222  // calculate an initial quaternion using the new yaw value
4223  initQuat.from_euler(roll, pitch, yaw);
4224  } else {
4225  initQuat = state.quat;
4226  }
4227 
4228  // calculate initial Tbn matrix and rotate Mag measurements into NED
4229  // to set initial NED magnetic field states
4230  initQuat.rotation_matrix(Tbn);
4231  state.earth_magfield = Tbn * magData;
4232 
4233  // align the NE earth magnetic field states with the published declination
4234  alignMagStateDeclination();
4235 
4236  // clear bad magnetometer status
4237  badMag = false;
4238  } else {
4239  initQuat.from_euler(roll, pitch, 0.0f);
4240  yawAligned = false;
4241  }
4242 
4243  // return attitude quaternion
4244  return initQuat;
4245 }
4246 
4247 // this function is used to do a forced alignment of the yaw angle to align with the horizontal velocity
4248 // vector from GPS. It is used to align the yaw angle after launch or takeoff.
4249 void NavEKF_core::alignYawGPS()
4250 {
4251  if ((sq(velNED[0]) + sq(velNED[1])) > 25.0f) {
4252  float roll;
4253  float pitch;
4254  float oldYaw;
4255  float newYaw;
4256  float yawErr;
4257  // get quaternion from existing filter states and calculate roll, pitch and yaw angles
4258  state.quat.to_euler(roll, pitch, oldYaw);
4259  // calculate course yaw angle
4260  oldYaw = atan2f(state.velocity.y,state.velocity.x);
4261  // calculate yaw angle from GPS velocity
4262  newYaw = atan2f(velNED[1],velNED[0]);
4263  // estimate the yaw error
4264  yawErr = wrap_PI(newYaw - oldYaw);
4265  // If the inertial course angle disagrees with the GPS by more than 45 degrees, we declare the compass as bad
4266  badMag = (fabsf(yawErr) > 0.7854f);
4267  // correct yaw angle using GPS ground course compass failed or if not previously aligned
4268  if (badMag || !yawAligned) {
4269  // correct the yaw angle
4270  newYaw = oldYaw + yawErr;
4271  // calculate new filter quaternion states from Euler angles
4272  state.quat.from_euler(roll, pitch, newYaw);
4273  // the yaw angle is now aligned so update its status
4274  yawAligned = true;
4275  // reset the position and velocity states
4276  ResetPosition();
4277  ResetVelocity();
4278  // reset the covariance for the quaternion, velocity and position states
4279  // zero the matrix entries
4280  zeroRows(P,0,9);
4281  zeroCols(P,0,9);
4282  // quaternions - TODO maths that sets them based on different roll, yaw and pitch uncertainties
4283  P[0][0] = 1.0e-9f;
4284  P[1][1] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4285  P[2][2] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4286  P[3][3] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4287  // velocities - we could have a big error coming out of constant position mode due to GPS lag
4288  P[4][4] = 400.0f;
4289  P[5][5] = P[4][4];
4290  P[6][6] = sq(0.7f);
4291  // positions - we could have a big error coming out of constant position mode due to GPS lag
4292  P[7][7] = 400.0f;
4293  P[8][8] = P[7][7];
4294  P[9][9] = sq(5.0f);
4295  }
4296  // Update magnetic field states if the magnetometer is bad
4297  if (badMag) {
4298  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4299  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4300  calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4301  }
4302  }
4303 }
4304 
4305 // This function is used to do a forced alignment of the wind velocity
4306 // states so that they are set to the reciprocal of the ground speed
4307 // and scaled to STARTUP_WIND_SPEED m/s. This is used when launching a
4308 // fly-forward vehicle without an airspeed sensor on the assumption
4309 // that launch will be into wind and STARTUP_WIND_SPEED is
4310 // representative of typical launch wind
4311 void NavEKF_core::setWindVelStates()
4312 {
4313  float gndSpd = pythagorous2(state.velocity.x, state.velocity.y);
4314  if (gndSpd > 4.0f) {
4315  // set the wind states to be the reciprocal of the velocity and scale
4316  float scaleFactor = STARTUP_WIND_SPEED / gndSpd;
4317  state.wind_vel.x = - state.velocity.x * scaleFactor;
4318  state.wind_vel.y = - state.velocity.y * scaleFactor;
4319  // reinitialise the wind state covariances
4320  zeroRows(P,14,15);
4321  zeroCols(P,14,15);
4322  P[14][14] = 64.0f;
4323  P[15][15] = P[14][14];
4324  }
4325 }

4327 // return the transformation matrix from XYZ (body) to NED axes
4328 void NavEKF_core::getRotationBodyToNED(Matrix3f &mat) const
4329 {
4330  Vector3f trim = _ahrs->get_trim();
4331  state.quat.rotation_matrix(mat);
4332  mat.rotateXYinv(trim);
4333 }

4335 // return the innovations for the NED Pos, NED Vel, XYZ Mag and Vtas measurements
4336 void NavEKF_core::getInnovations(Vector3f &velInnov, Vector3f &posInnov, Vector3f &magInnov, float &tasInnov) const
4337 {
4338  velInnov.x = innovVelPos[0];
4339  velInnov.y = innovVelPos[1];
4340  velInnov.z = innovVelPos[2];
4341  posInnov.x = innovVelPos[3];
4342  posInnov.y = innovVelPos[4];
4343  posInnov.z = innovVelPos[5];
4344  magInnov.x = 1e3f*innovMag[0]; // Convert back to sensor units
4345  magInnov.y = 1e3f*innovMag[1]; // Convert back to sensor units
4346  magInnov.z = 1e3f*innovMag[2]; // Convert back to sensor units
4347  tasInnov = innovVtas;
4348 }

4350 // return the innovation consistency test ratios for the velocity, position, magnetometer and true airspeed measurements
4351 // this indicates the amount of margin available when tuning the various error traps
4352 // also return the amount of NE position shift due to the last position reset
4353 void NavEKF_core::getVariances(float &velVar, float &posVar, float &hgtVar, Vector3f &magVar, float &tasVar, Vector2f &offset) const
4354 {
4355  velVar = sqrtf(velTestRatio);
4356  posVar = sqrtf(posTestRatio);
4357  hgtVar = sqrtf(hgtTestRatio);
4358  magVar.x = sqrtf(magTestRatio.x);
4359  magVar.y = sqrtf(magTestRatio.y);
4360  magVar.z = sqrtf(magTestRatio.z);
4361  tasVar = sqrtf(tasTestRatio);
4362  offset = posResetNE;
4363 }

4564 /*
4565 return the filter fault status as a bitmasked integer
4566  0 = quaternions are NaN
4567  1 = velocities are NaN
4568  2 = badly conditioned X magnetometer fusion
4569  3 = badly conditioned Y magnetometer fusion
4570  4 = badly conditioned Z magnetometer fusion
4571  5 = badly conditioned airspeed fusion
4572  6 = badly conditioned synthetic sideslip fusion
4573  7 = filter is not initialised
4574 */
4575 void NavEKF_core::getFilterFaults(uint8_t &faults) const
4576 {
4577  faults = (state.quat.is_nan()<<0 |
4578  state.velocity.is_nan()<<1 |
4579  faultStatus.bad_xmag<<2 |
4580  faultStatus.bad_ymag<<3 |
4581  faultStatus.bad_zmag<<4 |
4582  faultStatus.bad_airspeed<<5 |
4583  faultStatus.bad_sideslip<<6 |
4584  !statesInitialised<<7);
4585 }

4594  5 = unassigned

4597 */

4607 /*
4608 return filter gps quality check status
4609 */
4610 void NavEKF_core::getFilterGpsStatus(nav_gps_status &faults) const
4611 {
4612  // init return value
4613  faults.value = 0;
4614 
4615  // set individual flags
4616  faults.flags.bad_sAcc = gpsCheckStatus.bad_sAcc; // reported speed accuracy is insufficient
4617  faults.flags.bad_hAcc = gpsCheckStatus.bad_hAcc; // reported horizontal position accuracy is insufficient
4618  faults.flags.bad_yaw = gpsCheckStatus.bad_yaw; // EKF heading accuracy is too large for GPS use
4619  faults.flags.bad_sats = gpsCheckStatus.bad_sats; // reported number of satellites is insufficient
4620  faults.flags.bad_VZ = gpsCheckStatus.bad_VZ; // GPS vertical velocity is inconsistent with the IMU and Baro measurements
4621  faults.flags.bad_horiz_drift = gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_drift; // GPS horizontal drift is too large to start using GPS (check assumes vehicle is static)
4622  faults.flags.bad_hdop = gpsCheckStatus.bad_hdop; // reported HDoP is too large to start using GPS
4623  faults.flags.bad_vert_vel = gpsCheckStatus.bad_vert_vel; // GPS vertical speed is too large to start using GPS (check assumes vehicle is static)
4624  faults.flags.bad_fix = gpsCheckStatus.bad_fix; // The GPS cannot provide the 3D fix required
4625  faults.flags.bad_horiz_vel = gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_vel; // The GPS horizontal speed is excessive (check assumes the vehicle is static)
4626 }
4627 
4628 /*
4629 return filter function status as a bitmasked integer
4630  0 = attitude estimate valid
4631  1 = horizontal velocity estimate valid
4632  2 = vertical velocity estimate valid
4633  3 = relative horizontal position estimate valid
4634  4 = absolute horizontal position estimate valid
4635  5 = vertical position estimate valid
4636  6 = terrain height estimate valid
4637  7 = constant position mode
4638 */
4639 void NavEKF_core::getFilterStatus(nav_filter_status &status) const
4640 {
4641  // init return value
4642  status.value = 0;
4643 
4644  bool doingFlowNav = (PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) && flowDataValid;
4645  bool doingWindRelNav = !tasTimeout && assume_zero_sideslip();
4646  bool doingNormalGpsNav = !posTimeout && (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE);
4647  bool notDeadReckoning = !constPosMode;
4648  bool someVertRefData = (!velTimeout && useGpsVertVel) || !hgtTimeout;
4649  bool someHorizRefData = !(velTimeout && posTimeout && tasTimeout) || doingFlowNav;
4650  bool optFlowNavPossible = flowDataValid && (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3);
4651  bool gpsNavPossible = !gpsNotAvailable && (frontend._fusionModeGPS <= 2) && gpsGoodToAlign;
4652  bool filterHealthy = healthy();
4653  bool gyroHealthy = checkGyroHealthPreFlight();
4654 
4655  // set individual flags
4656  status.flags.attitude = !state.quat.is_nan() && filterHealthy && gyroHealthy; // attitude valid (we need a better check)
4657  status.flags.horiz_vel = someHorizRefData && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // horizontal velocity estimate valid
4658  status.flags.vert_vel = someVertRefData && filterHealthy; // vertical velocity estimate valid
4659  status.flags.horiz_pos_rel = ((doingFlowNav && gndOffsetValid) || doingWindRelNav || doingNormalGpsNav) && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // relative horizontal position estimate valid
4660  status.flags.horiz_pos_abs = !gpsAidingBad && doingNormalGpsNav && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // absolute horizontal position estimate valid
4661  status.flags.vert_pos = !hgtTimeout && filterHealthy; // vertical position estimate valid
4662  status.flags.terrain_alt = gndOffsetValid && filterHealthy; // terrain height estimate valid
4663  status.flags.const_pos_mode = constPosMode && filterHealthy; // constant position mode
4664  status.flags.pred_horiz_pos_rel = (optFlowNavPossible || gpsNavPossible) && filterHealthy && gyroHealthy; // we should be able to estimate a relative position when we enter flight mode
4665  status.flags.pred_horiz_pos_abs = gpsNavPossible && filterHealthy && gyroHealthy; // we should be able to estimate an absolute position when we enter flight mode
4666  status.flags.takeoff_detected = takeOffDetected; // takeoff for optical flow navigation has been detected
4667  status.flags.takeoff = expectGndEffectTakeoff; // The EKF has been told to expect takeoff and is in a ground effect mitigation mode
4668  status.flags.touchdown = expectGndEffectTouchdown; // The EKF has been told to detect touchdown and is in a ground effect mitigation mode
4669  status.flags.using_gps = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime) < 4000;
4670  status.flags.gps_glitching = !gpsAccuracyGood; // The GPS is glitching
4671 }
4672 
4673 // send an EKF_STATUS message to GCS
4674 void NavEKF_core::send_status_report(mavlink_channel_t chan)
4675 {
4676  // get filter status
4677  nav_filter_status filt_state;
4678  getFilterStatus(filt_state);
4679 
4680  // prepare flags
4681  uint16_t flags = 0;
4682  if (filt_state.flags.attitude) { flags |= EKF_ATTITUDE; }
4683  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_vel) { flags |= EKF_VELOCITY_HORIZ; }
4684  if (filt_state.flags.vert_vel) { flags |= EKF_VELOCITY_VERT; }
4685  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_pos_rel) { flags |= EKF_POS_HORIZ_REL; }
4686  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_pos_abs) { flags |= EKF_POS_HORIZ_ABS; }
4687  if (filt_state.flags.vert_pos) { flags |= EKF_POS_VERT_ABS; }
4688  if (filt_state.flags.terrain_alt) { flags |= EKF_POS_VERT_AGL; }
4689  if (filt_state.flags.const_pos_mode) { flags |= EKF_CONST_POS_MODE; }
4690  if (filt_state.flags.pred_horiz_pos_rel) { flags |= EKF_PRED_POS_HORIZ_REL; }
4691  if (filt_state.flags.pred_horiz_pos_abs) { flags |= EKF_PRED_POS_HORIZ_ABS; }
4692 
4693  // get variances
4694  float velVar, posVar, hgtVar, tasVar;
4695  Vector3f magVar;
4696  Vector2f offset;
4697  getVariances(velVar, posVar, hgtVar, magVar, tasVar, offset);
4698 
4699  // send message
4700  mavlink_msg_ekf_status_report_send(chan, flags, velVar, posVar, hgtVar, magVar.length(), tasVar);
4701 
4702 }
4703 
4704 // Check arm status and perform required checks and mode changes
4705 void NavEKF_core::performArmingChecks()
4706 {
4707  // determine vehicle arm status and don't allow filter to arm until it has been running for long enough to stabilise
4708  prevVehicleArmed = vehicleArmed;
4709  vehicleArmed = (getVehicleArmStatus() && (imuSampleTime_ms - ekfStartTime_ms) > 1000);
4710 
4711  // check to see if arm status has changed and reset states if it has
4712  if (vehicleArmed != prevVehicleArmed) {
4713  // only reset the magnetic field and heading on the first arm. This prevents in-flight learning being forgotten for vehicles that do multiple short flights and disarm in-between.
4714  if (vehicleArmed && !firstArmComplete) {
4715  firstArmComplete = true;
4716  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4717  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4718  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4719  }
4720  // store vertical position at arming to use as a reference for ground relative cehcks
4721  if (vehicleArmed) {
4722  posDownAtArming = state.position.z;
4723  // save the gyro bias so that the in-flight gyro bias state limits can be adjusted to provide the same amount of offset change in either direction
4724  delAngBiasAtArming = state.gyro_bias;
4725  }
4726  // zero stored velocities used to do dead-reckoning
4727  heldVelNE.zero();
4728  // reset the flag that indicates takeoff for use by optical flow navigation
4729  takeOffDetected = false;
4730  // set various useage modes based on the condition at arming. These are then held until the vehicle is disarmed.
4731  if (!vehicleArmed) {
4732  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // When dis-armed, we only estimate orientation & height using the constant position mode
4733  posTimeout = true;
4734  velTimeout = true;
4735  constPosMode = true;
4736  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position when disarmed
4737  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
4738  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
4739  // initialise filtered altitude used to provide a takeoff reference to current baro on disarm
4740  // this reduces the time required for the filter to settle before the estimate can be used
4741  meaHgtAtTakeOff = hgtMea;
4742  // reset the vertical position state to faster recover from baro errors experienced during touchdown
4743  state.position.z = -hgtMea;
4744  // record the time we disarmed
4745  timeAtDisarm_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4746  // if the GPS is not glitching when we land, we reset the timer used to check GPS quality
4747  // timer is not set to zero to avoid triggering an automatic fail
4748  if (gpsAccuracyGood) {
4749  lastGpsVelFail_ms = 1;
4750  gpsGoodToAlign = true;
4751  }
4752  // we reset the GPS drift checks when disarming as the vehicle has been moving during flight
4753  gpsDriftNE = 0.0f;
4754  gpsVertVelFilt = 0.0f;
4755  gpsHorizVelFilt = 0.0f;
4756  } else if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3) { // arming when GPS useage has been prohibited
4757  if (optFlowDataPresent()) {
4758  PV_AidingMode = AID_RELATIVE; // we have optical flow data and can estimate all vehicle states
4759  posTimeout = true;
4760  velTimeout = true;
4761  constPosMode = false;
4762  } else {
4763  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // we don't have optical flow data and will only be able to estimate orientation and height
4764  posTimeout = true;
4765  velTimeout = true;
4766  constPosMode = true;
4767  }
4768  // Reset the last valid flow measurement time
4769  flowValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4770  // Reset the last valid flow fusion time
4771  prevFlowFuseTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4772  // this avoids issues casued by the time delay associated with arming that can trigger short timeouts
4773  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4774  // store the range finder measurement which will be used as a reference to detect when we have taken off
4775  rangeAtArming = rngMea;
4776  // set the time at which we arm to assist with takeoff detection
4777  timeAtArming_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4778  } else { // arming when GPS useage is allowed
4779  if (gpsNotAvailable) {
4780  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // we don't have have GPS data and will only be able to estimate orientation and height
4781  posTimeout = true;
4782  velTimeout = true;
4783  constPosMode = true;
4784  } else {
4785  PV_AidingMode = AID_ABSOLUTE; // we have GPS data and can estimate all vehicle states
4786  posTimeout = false;
4787  velTimeout = false;
4788  constPosMode = false;
4789  // we need to reset the GPS timers to prevent GPS timeout logic being invoked on entry into GPS aiding
4790  // this is becasue the EKF can be interrupted for an arbitrary amount of time during vehicle arming checks
4791  lastFixTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4792  secondLastFixTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4793  // reset the last valid position fix time to prevent unwanted activation of GPS glitch logic
4794  lastPosPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
4795  // reset the fail time to prevent premature reporting of loss of position accruacy
4796  lastPosFailTime = 0;
4797  }
4798  }
4799  if (vehicleArmed) {
4800  // Reset filter position to GPS when transitioning into flight mode
4801  // We need to do this becasue the vehicle may have moved since the EKF origin was set
4802  ResetPosition();
4803  StoreStatesReset();
4804  } else {
4805  // Reset all position and velocity states when transitioning out of flight mode
4806  // We need to do this becasue we are going into a mode that assumes zero position and velocity
4807  ResetVelocity();
4808  ResetPosition();
4809  StoreStatesReset();
4810  }
4811 
4812  }
4813 
4814  // Always turn aiding off when the vehicle is disarmed
4815  if (!vehicleArmed) {
4816  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
4817  posTimeout = true;
4818  velTimeout = true;
4819  // set constant position mode if aiding is inhibited
4820  constPosMode = true;
4821  }
4822 
4823 }

4882 // causes the EKF to compensate for expected barometer errors due to ground effect

4888 
4889 /*
4890  Monitor GPS data to see if quality is good enough to initialise the EKF
4891  Monitor magnetometer innovations to to see if the heading is good enough to use GPS
4892  Return true if all criteria pass for 10 seconds
4893  Once we have set the origin and are operating in GPS mode the status is set to true to avoid a race conditon with remote useage
4894  If we have landed with good GPS, then the status is assumed good for 5 seconds to allow transients to settle
4895 
4896  We also record the failure reason so that prearm_failure_reason() can give a good report to the user on why arming is failing
4897 */
4898 bool NavEKF_core::calcGpsGoodToAlign(void)
4899 {
4900  static struct Location gpsloc_prev; // LLH location of previous GPS measurement
4901 
4902  // calculate absolute difference between GPS vert vel and inertial vert vel
4903  float velDiffAbs;
4904  if (_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity()) {
4905  velDiffAbs = fabsf(velNED.z - state.velocity.z);
4906  } else {
4907  velDiffAbs = 0.0f;
4908  }
4909 
4910  // fail if velocity difference or reported speed accuracy greater than threshold
4911  bool gpsVelFail = ((velDiffAbs > 1.0f) || (gpsSpdAccuracy > 1.0f)) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_SPD_ERR);
4912 
4913  if (velDiffAbs > 1.0f) {
4914  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
4915  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4916  "GPS vert vel error %.1f", (double)velDiffAbs);
4917  gpsCheckStatus.bad_VZ = true;
4918  } else {
4919  gpsCheckStatus.bad_VZ = false;
4920  }
4921  if (gpsSpdAccuracy > 1.0f) {
4922  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
4923  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4924  "GPS speed error %.1f", (double)gpsSpdAccuracy);
4925  gpsCheckStatus.bad_sAcc = true;
4926  } else {
4927  gpsCheckStatus.bad_sAcc = false;
4928  }
4929 
4930  // fail if not enough sats
4931  bool numSatsFail = (_ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() < 6) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_NSATS);
4932  if (numSatsFail) {
4933  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string, sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4934  "GPS numsats %u (needs 6)", _ahrs->get_gps().num_sats());
4935  gpsCheckStatus.bad_sats = true;
4936  } else {
4937  gpsCheckStatus.bad_sats = false;
4938  }
4939 
4940  // fail if satellite geometry is poor
4941  bool hdopFail = (_ahrs->get_gps().get_hdop() > 250) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_HDOP);
4942  if (hdopFail) {
4943  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string, sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4944  "GPS HDOP %.1f (needs 2.5)", (double)(0.01f * _ahrs->get_gps().get_hdop()));
4945  gpsCheckStatus.bad_hdop = true;
4946  } else {
4947  gpsCheckStatus.bad_hdop = false;
4948  }
4949 
4950  // fail if horiziontal position accuracy not sufficient
4951  float hAcc = 0.0f;
4952  bool hAccFail;
4953  if (_ahrs->get_gps().horizontal_accuracy(hAcc)) {
4954  hAccFail = (hAcc > 5.0f) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_POS_ERR);
4955  } else {
4956  hAccFail = false;
4957  }
4958  if (hAccFail) {
4959  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
4960  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4961  "GPS horiz error %.1f", (double)hAcc);
4962  gpsCheckStatus.bad_hAcc = true;
4963  } else {
4964  gpsCheckStatus.bad_hAcc = false;
4965  }
4966 
4967  // If we have good magnetometer consistency and bad innovations for longer than 5 seconds then we reset heading and field states
4968  // This enables us to handle large changes to the external magnetic field environment that occur before arming
4969  if ((magTestRatio.x <= 1.0f && magTestRatio.y <= 1.0f) || !consistentMagData) {
4970  magYawResetTimer_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4971  }
4972  if (imuSampleTime_ms - magYawResetTimer_ms > 5000) {
4973  // reset heading and field states
4974  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4975  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4976  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4977  // reset timer to ensure that bad magnetometer data cannot cause a heading reset more often than every 5 seconds
4978  magYawResetTimer_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4979  }
4980 
4981  // fail if magnetometer innovations are outside limits indicating bad yaw
4982  // with bad yaw we are unable to use GPS
4983  bool yawFail;
4984  if ((magTestRatio.x > 1.0f || magTestRatio.y > 1.0f) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_YAW_ERR)) {
4985  yawFail = true;
4986  } else {
4987  yawFail = false;
4988  }
4989  if (yawFail) {
4990  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
4991  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
4992  "Mag yaw error x=%.1f y=%.1f",
4993  (double)magTestRatio.x,
4994  (double)magTestRatio.y);
4995  gpsCheckStatus.bad_yaw = true;
4996  } else {
4997  gpsCheckStatus.bad_yaw = false;
4998  }
4999 
5000  // Check for significant change in GPS position if disarmed which indicates bad GPS
5001  // Note: this assumes we are not flying from a moving vehicle, eg boat
5002  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location(); // Current location
5003  const float posFiltTimeConst = 10.0f; // time constant used to decay position drift
5004  // calculate time lapsesd since last GPS fix and limit to prevent numerical errors
5005  float deltaTime = constrain_float(float(lastFixTime_ms - secondLastFixTime_ms)*0.001f,0.01f,posFiltTimeConst);
5006  // Sum distance moved
5007  gpsDriftNE += location_diff(gpsloc_prev, gpsloc).length();
5008  gpsloc_prev = gpsloc;
5009  // Decay distance moved exponentially to zero
5010  gpsDriftNE *= (1.0f - deltaTime/posFiltTimeConst);
5011  // Clamp the fiter state to prevent excessive persistence of large transients
5012  gpsDriftNE = min(gpsDriftNE,10.0f);
5013  // Fail if more than 3 metres drift after filtering whilst pre-armed when the vehicle is supposed to be stationary
5014  // This corresponds to a maximum acceptable average drift rate of 0.3 m/s or single glitch event of 3m
5015  bool gpsDriftFail = (gpsDriftNE > 3.0f) && !vehicleArmed && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_POS_DRIFT);
5016  if (gpsDriftFail) {
5017  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
5018  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
5019  "GPS drift %.1fm (needs 3.0)", (double)gpsDriftNE);
5020  gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_drift = true;
5021  } else {
5022  gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_drift = false;
5023  }
5024 
5025  // Check that the vertical GPS vertical velocity is reasonable after noise filtering
5026  bool gpsVertVelFail;
5027  if (_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity() && !vehicleArmed) {
5028  // check that the average vertical GPS velocity is close to zero
5029  gpsVertVelFilt = 0.1f * velNED.z + 0.9f * gpsVertVelFilt;
5030  gpsVertVelFilt = constrain_float(gpsVertVelFilt,-10.0f,10.0f);
5031  gpsVertVelFail = (fabsf(gpsVertVelFilt) > 0.3f) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_VERT_SPD);
5032  } else if ((frontend._fusionModeGPS == 0) && !_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity()) {
5033  // If the EKF settings require vertical GPS velocity and the receiver is not outputting it, then fail
5034  gpsVertVelFail = true;
5035  } else {
5036  gpsVertVelFail = false;
5037  }
5038  if (gpsVertVelFail) {
5039  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
5040  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
5041  "GPS vertical speed %.2fm/s (needs 0.30)", (double)fabsf(gpsVertVelFilt));
5042  gpsCheckStatus.bad_vert_vel = true;
5043  } else {
5044  gpsCheckStatus.bad_vert_vel = false;
5045  }
5046 
5047  // Check that the horizontal GPS vertical velocity is reasonable after noise filtering
5048  bool gpsHorizVelFail;
5049  if (!vehicleArmed) {
5050  gpsHorizVelFilt = 0.1f * pythagorous2(velNED.x,velNED.y) + 0.9f * gpsHorizVelFilt;
5051  gpsHorizVelFilt = constrain_float(gpsHorizVelFilt,-10.0f,10.0f);
5052  gpsHorizVelFail = (fabsf(gpsHorizVelFilt) > 0.3f) && (frontend._gpsCheck & MASK_GPS_HORIZ_SPD);
5053  } else {
5054  gpsHorizVelFail = false;
5055  }
5056  if (gpsHorizVelFail) {
5057  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
5058  sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
5059  "GPS horizontal speed %.2fm/s (needs 0.30)", (double)gpsDriftNE);
5060  gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_vel = true;
5061  } else {
5062  gpsCheckStatus.bad_horiz_vel = false;
5063  }
5064 
5065  // return healthy if we already have an origin and are inflight to prevent a race condition when checking the status on the ground after landing
5066  // return healthy for a few seconds after landing so that filter disturbances don't fail the GPS
5067  static bool usingInFlight = false;
5068  usingInFlight = (vehicleArmed && validOrigin && !constPosMode) || (!vehicleArmed && usingInFlight && (imuSampleTime_ms - timeAtDisarm_ms) < 5000 && gpsAccuracyGood);
5069 
5070  if (usingInFlight) {
5071  return true;
5072  }
5073 
5074  if (lastGpsVelFail_ms == 0) {
5075  // first time through, start with a failure
5076  hal.util->snprintf(prearm_fail_string, sizeof(prearm_fail_string), "EKF warmup");
5077  lastGpsVelFail_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5078  }
5079 
5080  // record time of fail
5081  if (gpsVelFail || numSatsFail || hdopFail || hAccFail || yawFail || gpsDriftFail || gpsVertVelFail || gpsHorizVelFail) {
5082  lastGpsVelFail_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5083  }
5084 
5085  // continuous period without fail required to return healthy
5086  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsVelFail_ms > 10000) {
5087  return true;
5088  }
5089  return false;
5090 }
5091 
5092 // report the reason for why the backend is refusing to initialise
5093 const char *NavEKF_core::prearm_failure_reason(void) const
5094 {
5095  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsVelFail_ms > 10000) {
5096  // we are not failing
5097  return nullptr;
5098  }
5099  return prearm_fail_string;
5100 }
5101 
5102 // Read the range finder and take new measurements if available
5103 // Read at 20Hz and apply a median filter
5104 void NavEKF_core::readRangeFinder(void)
5105 {
5106  static float storedRngMeas[3];
5107  static uint32_t storedRngMeasTime_ms[3];
5108  static uint32_t lastRngMeasTime_ms = 0;
5109  static uint8_t rngMeasIndex = 0;
5110  uint8_t midIndex;
5111  uint8_t maxIndex;
5112  uint8_t minIndex;
5113  // get theoretical correct range when the vehicle is on the ground
5114  rngOnGnd = _rng.ground_clearance_cm() * 0.01f;
5115  if (_rng.status() == RangeFinder::RangeFinder_Good && (imuSampleTime_ms - lastRngMeasTime_ms) > 50) {
5116  // store samples and sample time into a ring buffer
5117  rngMeasIndex ++;
5118  if (rngMeasIndex > 2) {
5119  rngMeasIndex = 0;
5120  }
5121  storedRngMeasTime_ms[rngMeasIndex] = imuSampleTime_ms;
5122  storedRngMeas[rngMeasIndex] = _rng.distance_cm() * 0.01f;
5123  // check for three fresh samples and take median
5124  bool sampleFresh[3];
5125  for (uint8_t index = 0; index <= 2; index++) {
5126  sampleFresh[index] = (imuSampleTime_ms - storedRngMeasTime_ms[index]) < 500;
5127  }
5128  if (sampleFresh[0] && sampleFresh[1] && sampleFresh[2]) {
5129  if (storedRngMeas[0] > storedRngMeas[1]) {
5130  minIndex = 1;
5131  maxIndex = 0;
5132  } else {
5133  maxIndex = 0;
5134  minIndex = 1;
5135  }
5136  if (storedRngMeas[2] > storedRngMeas[maxIndex]) {
5137  midIndex = maxIndex;
5138  } else if (storedRngMeas[2] < storedRngMeas[minIndex]) {
5139  midIndex = minIndex;
5140  } else {
5141  midIndex = 2;
5142  }
5143  rngMea = max(storedRngMeas[midIndex],rngOnGnd);
5144  newDataRng = true;
5145  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5146  // recall vehicle states at mid sample time for range finder
5147  RecallStates(statesAtRngTime, storedRngMeasTime_ms[midIndex] - 25);
5148  } else if (!vehicleArmed) {
5149  // if not armed and no return, we assume on ground range
5150  rngMea = rngOnGnd;
5151  newDataRng = true;
5152  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5153  // assume synthetic measurement is at current time (no delay)
5154  statesAtRngTime = state;
5155  } else {
5156  newDataRng = false;
5157  }
5158  lastRngMeasTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5159  }
5160 }

5162 // Detect takeoff for optical flow navigation
5163 void NavEKF_core::detectOptFlowTakeoff(void)
5164 {
5165  if (vehicleArmed && !takeOffDetected && (imuSampleTime_ms - timeAtArming_ms) > 1000) {
5166  takeOffDetected = (takeOffDetected || (rngMea > (rangeAtArming + 0.1f)));
5167  }
5168 }

5170 // provides the height limit to be observed by the control loops
5171 // returns false if no height limiting is required
5172 // this is needed to ensure the vehicle does not fly too high when using optical flow navigation
5173 bool NavEKF_core::getHeightControlLimit(float &height) const
5174 {
5175  // only ask for limiting if we are doing optical flow navigation
5176  if (frontend._fusionModeGPS == 3) {
5177  // If are doing optical flow nav, ensure the height above ground is within range finder limits after accounting for vehicle tilt and control errors
5178  height = max(float(_rng.max_distance_cm()) * 0.007f - 1.0f, 1.0f);
5179  return true;
5180  } else {
5181  return false;
5182  }
5183 }

5191 // align the NE earth magnetic field states with the published declination
5192 void NavEKF_core::alignMagStateDeclination()
5193 {
5194  // get the magnetic declination
5195  float magDecAng = use_compass() ? _ahrs->get_compass()->get_declination() : 0;
5196 
5197  // rotate the NE values so that the declination matches the published value
5198  Vector3f initMagNED = state.earth_magfield;
5199  float magLengthNE = pythagorous2(initMagNED.x,initMagNED.y);
5200  state.earth_magfield.x = magLengthNE * cosf(magDecAng);
5201  state.earth_magfield.y = magLengthNE * sinf(magDecAng);
5202 }

5219 
5220 // return the amount of NE velocity change due to the last velocity reset in metres/sec
5221 // returns the time of the last reset or 0 if no reset has ever occurred
5222 uint32_t NavEKF_core::getLastVelNorthEastReset(Vector2f &vel) const
5223 {
5224  vel = velResetNE;
5225  return lastVelReset_ms;
5226 }

5228 // Check for signs of bad gyro health before flight
5229 bool NavEKF_core::checkGyroHealthPreFlight(void) const
5230 {
5231  bool retVar;
5232  if (hal.util->get_soft_armed()) {
5233  // Always return true if we are flying (use arm status as a surrogate for flying)
5234  retVar = true;
5235  } else if
5236  (state.gyro_bias.x < 0.5f*MAX_GYRO_BIAS*dtIMUavg &&
5237  state.gyro_bias.y < 0.5f*MAX_GYRO_BIAS*dtIMUavg &&
5238  state.gyro_bias.z < 0.5f*MAX_GYRO_BIAS*dtIMUavg &&
5239  posTestRatio < 0.1f) {
5240  // If the synthetic position innovations are too high or the estimated gyro bias exceeds 50% of the available adjustment we declare the gyro as unhealthy
5241  // this condition is likely caused by excessive gyro bias and the operator should be prompted to perform a gyro calibration and reset.
5242  retVar = true;
5243  } else {
5244  retVar = false;
5245  }
5246  return retVar;
5247 }

5249 // returns true of the EKF thinks the GPS is glitching or unavailable
5250 bool NavEKF_core::getGpsGlitchStatus(void) const
5251 {
5252  return !gpsAccuracyGood;
5253 }

5255 // update inflight calculaton that determines if GPS data is good enough for reliable navigation
5256 void NavEKF_core::calcGpsGoodForFlight(void)
5257 {
5258  // use a simple criteria based on the GPS receivers claimed speed accuracy and the EKF innovation consistency checks
5259  static bool gpsSpdAccPass = false;
5260  static bool ekfInnovationsPass = false;
5261 
5262  // set up varaibles and constants used by filter that is applied to GPS speed accuracy
5263  const float alpha1 = 0.2f; // coefficient for first stage LPF applied to raw speed accuracy data
5264  const float tau = 10.0f; // time constant (sec) of peak hold decay
5265  static float lpfFilterState = 0.0f; // first stage LPF filter state
5266  static float peakHoldFilterState = 0.0f; // peak hold with exponential decay filter state
5267  static uint32_t lastTime_ms = 0;
5268  if (lastTime_ms == 0) {
5269  lastTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5270  }
5271  float dtLPF = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastTime_ms) * 1e-3f;
5272  lastTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5273  float alpha2 = constrain_float(dtLPF/tau,0.0f,1.0f);
5274 
5275  // get the receivers reported speed accuracy
5276  float gpsSpdAccRaw;
5277  if (!_ahrs->get_gps().speed_accuracy(gpsSpdAccRaw)) {
5278  gpsSpdAccRaw = 0.0f;
5279  }
5280 
5281  // filter the raw speed accuracy using a LPF
5282  lpfFilterState = constrain_float((alpha1 * gpsSpdAccRaw + (1.0f - alpha1) * lpfFilterState),0.0f,10.0f);
5283 
5284  // apply a peak hold filter to the LPF output
5285  peakHoldFilterState = max(lpfFilterState,((1.0f - alpha2) * peakHoldFilterState));
5286 
5287  // Apply a threshold test with hysteresis to the filtered GPS speed accuracy data
5288  if (peakHoldFilterState > 1.5f ) {
5289  gpsSpdAccPass = false;
5290  } else if(peakHoldFilterState < 1.0f) {
5291  gpsSpdAccPass = true;
5292  }
5293 
5294  // Apply a threshold test with hysteresis to the normalised position and velocity innovations
5295  // Require a fail for one second and a pass for 10 seconds to transition
5296  static uint32_t lastInnovPassTime_ms = 0;
5297  static uint32_t lastInnovFailTime_ms = 0;
5298  if (lastInnovFailTime_ms == 0) {
5299  lastInnovFailTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5300  lastInnovPassTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5301  }
5302  if (velTestRatio < 1.0f && posTestRatio < 1.0f) {
5303  lastInnovPassTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5304  } else if (velTestRatio > 0.7f || posTestRatio > 0.7f) {
5305  lastInnovFailTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5306  }
5307  if ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastInnovPassTime_ms) > 1000) {
5308  ekfInnovationsPass = false;
5309  } else if ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastInnovFailTime_ms) > 10000) {
5310  ekfInnovationsPass = true;
5311  }
5312 
5313  // both GPS speed accuracy and EKF innovations must pass
5314  gpsAccuracyGood = gpsSpdAccPass && ekfInnovationsPass;
5315 }
